INSERT INTO `lessons` VALUES (113,2,'Introducción a RAIO','introduccion-a-raio','Comienza aquí',1,1,'Sigue estos pasos para comenzar correctamente y aprovechar al máximo el programa 👇','# 🚀 Primeros pasos\n\nSigue estos pasos para comenzar correctamente y aprovechar al máximo el programa 👇\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 **Paso 1 · Únete a la comunidad de Facebook**\n\nForma parte de nuestra comunidad de estudiantes, accede a coachings grupales y conéctate con otros alumnos.\n\n👉 [**Ingresar a la comunidad de Facebook**](https://www.facebook.com/groups/646967055825118/)\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 **Paso 2 · Únete al grupo de WhatsApp**\n\nRecibe avisos importantes, recordatorios y mantente informado en tiempo real.\n\n👉 [**Ingresar al grupo de WhatsApp**](https://group.wha.link/boyRNe)\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 **Paso 3 · Completa el formulario**\n\nEste paso es importante para conocerte mejor y darte el soporte adecuado durante el programa.\n\n📝 **Completa el formulario cuando tengas unos minutos y sin interrupciones.**','[{\"label\":\"**Ingresar a la comunidad de Facebook**\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/groups\\/646967055825118\\/\",\"description\":\"Enlace externo importado desde las notas.\"},{\"label\":\"**Ingresar al grupo de WhatsApp**\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/group.wha.link\\/boyRNe\",\"description\":\"Enlace externo importado desde las notas.\"},{\"label\":\"Video original en Drive\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/open?id=1ISADDu-4GkIBdmYVudcd6pHWLIOusYgC&usp=drive_fs\",\"description\":\"Enlace original exportado desde Notion.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/introduccion-a-raio.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/introduccion-a-raio/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/introduccion-a-raio/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/introduccion-a-raio/subtitle-en.vtt',3333,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:13','2026-05-08 08:04:13'),(114,2,'Preguntas Frecuentes','preguntas-frecuentes','Comienza aquí',1,2,'Las secciones del curso están divididas en dos partes :','---\n\n# 📘 FAQ · Preguntas Frecuentes\n\n---\n\n## 🎓 ¿Cómo funcionan las clases del programa?\n\nLas secciones del curso están divididas en **dos partes**:\n\n- **La clase** (video)\n- **La historia**\n\nTodo el material está **pregrabado y es descargable**, para que puedas estudiar **a tu ritmo**, desde cualquier dispositivo y lugar.\n\n### 🔹 Paso a paso del método\n\n1. **Empiezas viendo la clase**\n    - Aprendes el inglés que aparecerá en la historia:\n        - vocabulario\n        - gramática\n        - pronunciación\n    - Explico exactamente **qué debes hacer** en cada paso.\n    - Recomiendo activar **subtítulos en español** para entender perfectamente las instrucciones.\n        - También puedes usar **subtítulos en inglés** si quieres desafiarte un poco.\n2. **Luego trabajas la historia en 3 etapas**\n    - 🟢 Con traducción, hasta entenderla completamente\n    - 🟡 Sin traducción, hasta entenderla “con los ojos cerrados”\n    - 🔵 Práctica oral: respondes preguntas en voz alta sobre la historia, hasta hacerlo correctamente y sin esfuerzo\n\n> 🧠 Ten paciencia: es normal repetir varias veces cada paso. Eso es parte del proceso.\n> \n\n👉 **Solo cuando logres el objetivo de la sección** (responder todas las preguntas correctamente con los ojos cerrados), avanzas a la siguiente.\n\nCada sección **aumenta el nivel de dificultad**.\n\n📌 La última sección de cada capítulo incluye un **resumen con pasos de acción claros**.\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 ¿Cómo debo estudiar para obtener los mejores resultados?\n\nLos resultados más rápidos se logran combinando:\n\n- 📘 Estudio diario del curso\n- 📱 Revisión de frases en la app **RAIO**\n    \n    > (explicado en Sección 6, Capítulo 1)\n    > \n- 🗣️ Sesiones de conversación para ganar fluidez\n- 🎯 Clases privadas para feedback personalizado\n    \n    > (Solo miembros UNLIMITED)\n    > \n\nSi aún no tienes activas las sesiones de conversación o clases privadas, **contáctanos y te ayudamos**.\n\n### 🗓️ Distribución recomendada del tiempo\n\n- ✅ 1 sección del curso por día\n- ✅ Revisar frases en RAIO todos los días\n- ✅ 1–2 sesiones de conversación por semana *(UNLIMITED)*\n- ✅ 1–2 clases privadas por semana *(UNLIMITED)*\n\n---\n\n## ⏰ ¿Cuánto tiempo debo dedicarle al día?\n\nDepende de qué tan rápido quieras avanzar.\n\n📊 **Promedio de nuestros estudiantes:**\n\n- ⏱️ Entre **20 y 60 minutos diarios**\n\n> ⚠️ Lo más importante no es el tiempo, sino la constancia y la disciplina.\n> \n\n🎯 **Garantía:**\n\nSi completas el curso siguiendo la metodología y no aprendes inglés, **te devolvemos el doble de lo que pagaste**.\n\n### ⏳ Si tienes poco tiempo:\n\nConcéntrate en:\n\n- Avanzar por las secciones\n- Revisar tus frases en RAIO diariamente\n\nLas sesiones de conversación y clases privadas son **complementarias**.\n\n---\n\n## 📈 ¿En cuánto tiempo aprendo inglés?\n\nAprendes desde el **primer día**.\n\nCada semana notarás avances si sigues la metodología.\n\nLa fluidez total suele lograrse en promedio:\n\n- 🕒 **3–4 meses** → 2 horas/día\n- 🕒 **6–8 meses** → 1 hora/día\n- 🕒 **12–16 meses** → 30 minutos/día\n\n⏳ Tienes **acceso de por vida**, así que **no hay prisa**.\n\nLa clave es **terminar el curso**, tarde o temprano.\n\n---\n\n## 🧪 ¿Cómo miden mi progreso?\n\nAl final de cada capítulo:\n\n- 📹 Subes un **video hablando en inglés**\n- Lo evaluamos internamente\n- Usamos ese material para darte feedback en tus clases privadas *(UNLIMITED)*\n\n👉 Si deseas evaluar tu progreso **sin profesor**, sigue las instrucciones de:\n\n- Sección 12\n- Sección 18\n    \n    (Capítulo 2)\n    \n\n---\n\n## 🆘 ¿Cómo obtengo ayuda?\n\nPuedes contactarnos por:\n\n- 📧 Email: **soporte@kaleanders.com**\n- 📱 WhatsApp: **+1 (954) 951-9586**\n\n🕐 Estamos disponibles **24/7**.\n\n### Otras formas de ayuda\n\n- 💬 Preguntar en los **coachings grupales**\n- 👥 Interactuar con otros estudiantes en el grupo de Facebook\n    \n    *(PRO y UNLIMITED)*\n    \n\n> Muchos estudiantes ya terminaron el curso y están felices de ayudarte.\n> \n\n✨ **No dejes que los obstáculos frenen tu proceso.**\n\n🔥 *¡La fluidez no espera a nadie!*\n\n---\n\n## 👥 ¿Cómo unirme al grupo de estudiantes en Facebook?\n\n1. Ve a la parte superior de la página\n2. Haz clic en **“Student Group”** *(PRO y UNLIMITED)*\n3. Solicita acceso con el **mismo email de compra**\n\n⏱️ Normalmente aceptamos solicitudes en menos de **24 horas**.\n\n---\n\n## 🎤 ¿Cómo unirme a los coaching grupales?\n\n*(PRO y UNLIMITED)*\n\n- Se realizan **dentro del grupo de Facebook**\n- 📅 Cada semana:\n    - 2 sesiones con coaches\n    - 1 sesión conmigo (Kale), cada dos semanas\n\n📩 **Todos los lunes** recibirás un email con los horarios de la semana.\n\nTambién puedes verlos en el **banner superior** de la comunidad.\n\n🎥 ¿No puedes asistir en vivo?\n\nNo hay problema:\n\n- Las sesiones quedan grabadas\n- Busca la palabra **“coaching”** dentro del grupo\n\n---\n\n## 🎬 ¿Debo ver los videos sin subtítulos?\n\nComo te sientas más cómodo.\n\n✔️ Lo importante es:\n\n- Entender bien las indicaciones\n- Seguir el método paso a paso\n\n---\n\n## 📜 ¿Hay certificado?\n\nSí, puedes solicitar un **certificado digital** al finalizar el curso.\n\n💡 Pero recuerda:\n\nEl mejor certificado será **tu capacidad de hablar inglés con fluidez**.\n\nEso es nuestra prioridad.\n\n---\n\n## 💸 ¿Cómo puedo solicitar un reembolso?\n\nEspero que nunca sea necesario, porque mi prioridad #1 es que **aprendas inglés**.\n\nPero si decides hacerlo:\n\n1. Escríbenos por:\n    - 📧 soporte@kaleanders.com\n    - 📱 WhatsApp +1 (954) 951-9586\n2. Incluye:\n    - Nombre completo\n    - Email de compra\n\nNuestro equipo intentará ayudarte a continuar.\n\nSi no es posible, te enviaremos el **enlace oficial** para el reembolso.\n\n### ⚠️ Condiciones importantes\n\n- Debes estar dentro del **periodo de garantía (14 días)**\n- Procesamos solicitudes en menos de **24 horas**\n- El dinero puede tardar hasta **15 días hábiles** según tu banco\n\n🚫 **NO solicites el reembolso por tu banco**\n\nEse proceso puede tardar hasta **3 meses**.\n\n👉 Contáctanos directamente y te ayudamos **sin complicaciones**.\n\n---\n\nSi quieres, en el siguiente mensaje puedo:\n\n- Adaptarlo a **Notion con toggles (desplegables)**\n- Convertir cada pregunta en **bloques FAQ premium**\n- O darle un **tono más comercial o más cercano**\n\nTú me dices 👍','[]',NULL,NULL,'media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/preguntas-frecuentes/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/preguntas-frecuentes/subtitle-en.vtt',NULL,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:13','2026-05-08 08:04:13'),(115,2,'Presenting Yourself','presenting-yourself','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,1,'Escucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.','---\n\n# 👤 Presenting Yourself\n\n**Section 1 · Chapter 1**\n\n---\n\n> 🎥 Video (Clase)\n> \n> \n> https://drive.google.com/open?id=1coizDkzay0sG6Sq37_EbwFMhN4Ybaiz0&usp=drive_fs\n> \n\n> 💡 Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n> \n\n---\n\n## ✅ 1) Escucha con traducción\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n🎧 **Audio:** *Normal version*\n\n[Chapter 1 - Story 1 - Presenting yourself - Normal version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/presenting-yourself/chapter-1-story-1-presenting-yourself-normal-version.mp3)\n\n---\n\n### 📖 Historia (con traducción)\n\n- ***Hello, my name is David.***\n    \n    *Hola, mi nombre es David.*\n    \n- ***I am thirty-two years old.***\n    \n    *Tengo treinta y dos años de edad.*\n    \n- ***I live in Colombia.***\n    \n    *Vivo en Colombia.*\n    \n- ***I am from the United States.***\n    \n    *Soy de Estados Unidos.*\n    \n- ***I am married.***\n    \n    *Estoy casado.*\n    \n- ***My wife and I have three children.***\n    \n    *Mi esposa y yo tenemos tres hijos.*\n    \n- ***I have two sons and one daughter.***\n    \n    *Tengo dos hijos y una hija.*\n    \n- ***Their names are John, Kevin, and Ann.***\n    \n    *Sus nombres son John, Kevin y Ann.*\n    \n- ***We also have a dog.***\n    \n    *También tenemos un perro.*\n    \n- ***The dog’s name is Buster.***\n    \n    *El nombre del perro es Buster.*\n    \n- ***I am a postman.***\n    \n    *Soy cartero.*\n    \n- ***I deliver the mail each day.***\n    \n    *Entrego el correo todos los días.*\n    \n- ***I like to eat American food.***\n    \n    *Me gusta comer comida americana.*\n    \n- ***Hot dogs are delicious.***\n    \n    *Los perros calientes son deliciosos.*\n    \n- ***I also like to cook.***\n    \n    *También me gusta cocinar.*\n    \n- ***Cakes are my favorite food to bake.***\n    \n    *Los pasteles son mi comida favorita para hornear.*\n    \n- ***Cakes are also my favorite food to eat.***\n    \n    *Los pasteles también son mi comida favorita para comer.*\n    \n- ***I also enjoy exercising.***\n    \n    *También disfruto hacer ejercicio.*\n    \n- ***I like to run and hike.***\n    \n    *Me gusta correr y hacer senderismo.*\n    \n- ***After eating hotdogs and cakes, I need to exercise.***\n    \n    *Después de comer perros calientes y pasteles, necesito hacer ejercicio.*\n    \n\n---\n\n## ✅ 2) Escucha sin traducción\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia **con los ojos cerrados**.\n\n🎧 **Audio:** *Normal version*\n\n[Chapter 1 - Story 1 - Presenting yourself - Normal version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/presenting-yourself/chapter-1-story-1-presenting-yourself-normal-version.mp3)\n\n---\n\n### 🎯 Historia (solo inglés)\n\n- ***Hello, my name is David.***\n- ***I am thirty-two years old.***\n- ***I live in Colombia.***\n- ***I am from the United States.***\n- ***I am married.***\n- ***My wife and I have three children.***\n- ***I have two sons and one daughter.***\n- ***Their names are John, Kevin, and Ann.***\n- ***We also have a dog.***\n- ***The dog’s name is Buster.***\n- ***I am a postman.***\n- ***I deliver the mail each day.***\n- ***I like to eat American food.***\n- ***Hot dogs are delicious.***\n- ***I also like to cook.***\n- ***Cakes are my favorite food to bake.***\n- ***Cakes are also my favorite food to eat.***\n- ***I also enjoy exercising.***\n- ***I like to run and hike.***\n- ***After eating hotdogs and cakes, I need to exercise.***\n\n---\n\n## ✅ 3) Escucha y practica responder\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder **correctamente**, **a tiempo**, **en voz alta** y **con los ojos cerrados**.\n\n🎧 **Audio:** *Interactive version*\n\n[Chapter 1 - Story 1 - Presenting yourself - Interactive version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/presenting-yourself/chapter-1-story-1-presenting-yourself-interactive-version.mp3)\n\n---\n\n### 🗣️ Práctica (preguntas y respuestas)\n\n- ***Hello, my name is David.***\n    \n    *Is my name David?* **[YES/NO]**, *it is.*\n    \n- ***I am thirty-two years old.***\n    \n    *Am I thirty-two years old?* **[YES/NO]**, *I am.*\n    \n- ***I live in Colombia.***\n    \n    *Do I live in the United States?* **[YES/NO]**, *I don’t.*\n    \n- ***I am from the United States.***\n    \n    *Am I from the United States?* **[YES/NO]**, *I am.*\n    \n- ***I am married.***\n    \n    *Am I single?* **[YES/NO]**, *I’m not.*\n    \n- ***My wife and I have three children.***\n    \n    *Do I have three children?* **[YES/NO]**, *I do.*\n    \n- ***I have two sons and one daughter.***\n    \n    *Do I have three sons?* **[YES/NO]**, *I don’t.*\n    \n- ***Their names are John, Kevin, and Ann.***\n    \n    *Is my daughter’s name Ann?* **[YES/NO]**, *it is.*\n    \n- ***We also have a dog.***\n    \n    *Do I have a cat?* **[YES/NO]**, *I don’t.*\n    \n- ***The dog’s name is Buster.***\n    \n    *Is my dog’s name Fido?* **[YES/NO]**, *it isn’t.*\n    \n- ***I work as a postman.***\n    \n    *Do I have a job?* **[YES/NO]**, *I do.*\n    \n- ***I deliver the mail each day.***\n    \n    *Do I deliver the mail?* **[YES/NO]**, *I do.*\n    \n- ***I like to eat American food.***\n    \n    *Do I like to eat Italian food?* **[YES/NO]**, *I don’t.*\n    \n- ***Hot dogs are delicious.***\n    \n    *Do I think hot dogs are delicious?* **[YES/NO]**, *I do.*\n    \n- ***I also like to cook.***\n    \n    *Is cooking something I like to do?* **[YES/NO]**, *it is.*\n    \n- ***Cakes are my favorite food to bake.***\n    \n    *Can I bake a cake?* **[YES/NO]**, *I can.*\n    \n- ***Cakes are also my favorite food to eat.***\n    \n    *Are donuts my favorite food to eat?* **[YES/NO]**, *they aren’t.*\n    \n- ***I also enjoy exercising.***\n    \n    *Do I enjoy exercising?* **[YES/NO]**, *I do.*\n    \n- ***I like to run and hike.***\n    \n    *Do I like to swim?* **[YES/NO]**, *I don’t.*\n    \n- ***After eating hotdogs and cakes, I need to exercise.***\n    \n    *After eating cake, do I need to sleep?* **[YES/NO]**, *I don’t.*\n    \n\n---\n\n> ⚠️ IMPORTANTE\n> \n> \n> Solo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder **todas las preguntas**:\n> \n> ✅ de forma correcta · ✅ en voz alta · ✅ a tiempo · ✅ sin mirar el texto\n> \n\n---','[{\"label\":\"Video original en Drive\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/open?id=1coizDkzay0sG6Sq37_EbwFMhN4Ybaiz0&usp=drive_fs\",\"description\":\"Enlace original exportado desde Notion.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter 1 - Story 1 - Presenting yourself - Normal version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/presenting-yourself\\/chapter-1-story-1-presenting-yourself-normal-version.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter 1 - Story 1 - Presenting yourself - Interactive version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/presenting-yourself\\/chapter-1-story-1-presenting-yourself-interactive-version.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/presenting-yourself.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/presenting-yourself/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/presenting-yourself/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/presenting-yourself/subtitle-en.vtt',3333,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:14','2026-05-08 08:04:14'),(116,2,'Family','family','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,2,'Escucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.','---\n\n# 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 Family\n\n**Section 2 · Chapter 1**\n\n---\n\n> 🎥 Video (Clase)\n> \n> \n> https://drive.google.com/open?id=1jHb_SzqBr_ysBiRtsDUHfGWSQ92XN04y&usp=drive_fs\n> \n\n> 💡 Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n> \n\n---\n\n## ✅ 1) Escucha con traducción\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n🎧 **Audio:** *Normal version*\n\n[Chapter 1 - Story 2 - Family - Normal version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/family/chapter-1-story-2-family-normal-version.mp3)\n\n**Velocidad sugerida:** 1x\n\n---\n\n### 📖 Historia (con traducción)\n\n- ***I have a huge family.***\n    \n    *Tengo una familia enorme.*\n    \n- ***I have five brothers and six sisters.***\n    \n    *Tengo cinco hermanos y seis hermanas.*\n    \n- ***I have a mother and father. They are my parents.***\n    \n    *Tengo una madre y un padre. Ellos son mis padres.*\n    \n- ***I have a grandmother. She is 84 years old.***\n    \n    *Tengo una abuela. Tiene 84 años.*\n    \n- ***My oldest sister has one son.***\n    \n    *Mi hermana mayor tiene un hijo.*\n    \n- ***He is my nephew.***\n    \n    *Es mi sobrino.*\n    \n- ***We live in Lima, Peru.***\n    \n    *Vivimos en Lima, Perú.*\n    \n- ***My mother has a brother.***\n    \n    *Mi madre tiene un hermano.*\n    \n- ***He is my uncle.***\n    \n    *Es mi tío.*\n    \n- ***My father has a sister.***\n    \n    *Mi padre tiene una hermana.*\n    \n- ***And she is my aunt.***\n    \n    *Y ella es mi tía.*\n    \n- ***My aunt and uncle live outside the city.***\n    \n    *Mi tía y mi tío viven fuera de la ciudad.*\n    \n- ***My aunt has one daughter.***\n    \n    *Mi tía tiene una hija.*\n    \n- ***She is my cousin.***\n    \n    *Es mi prima.*\n    \n- ***I like to spend time with my family.***\n    \n    *Me gusta pasar tiempo con mi familia.*\n    \n- ***I like to eat with my family.***\n    \n    *Me gusta comer con mi familia.*\n    \n- ***My family likes to play soccer.***\n    \n    *A mi familia le gusta jugar al fútbol.*\n    \n- ***My brothers and sisters are good players.***\n    \n    *Mis hermanos y hermanas son buenos jugadores.*\n    \n- ***My father and mother like to watch us play.***\n    \n    *A mi padre y a mi madre les gusta vernos jugar.*\n    \n- ***My parents cheer when we play well.***\n    \n    *Mis padres nos animan cuando jugamos bien.*\n    \n\n---\n\n## ✅ 2) Escucha sin traducción\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia **con los ojos cerrados**.\n\n🎧 **Audio:** *Normal version*\n\n[Chapter 1 - Story 2 - Family - Normal version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/family/chapter-1-story-2-family-normal-version.mp3)\n\n**Velocidad sugerida:** 1x\n\n---\n\n### 🎯 Historia (solo inglés)\n\n- ***I have a huge family.***\n- ***I have five brothers and six sisters.***\n- ***I have a mother and father. They are my parents.***\n- ***I have a grandmother. She is 84 years old.***\n- ***My oldest sister has one son.***\n- ***He is my nephew.***\n- ***We live in Lima, Peru.***\n- ***My mother has a brother.***\n- ***He is my uncle.***\n- ***My father has a sister.***\n- ***And she is my aunt.***\n- ***My aunt and uncle live outside the city.***\n- ***My aunt has one daughter.***\n- ***She is my cousin.***\n- ***I like to spend time with my family.***\n- ***I like to eat with my family.***\n- ***My family likes to play soccer.***\n- ***My brothers and sisters are good players.***\n- ***My father and mother like to watch us play.***\n- ***My parents cheer when we play well.***\n\n---\n\n## ✅ 3) Escucha y practica responder\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder **correctamente**, **a tiempo**, **en voz alta** y **con los ojos cerrados**.\n\n🎧 **Audio:** *Interactive version*\n\n[Chapter 1 - Story 2 - Family - Interactive version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/family/chapter-1-story-2-family-interactive-version.mp3)\n\n**Velocidad sugerida:** 1x\n\n---\n\n### 🗣️ Práctica (preguntas y respuestas)\n\n- ***I have a huge family.***\n    \n    *Do I have a small family?* **[YES/NO]**, *I don’t.*\n    \n- ***I have five brothers and six sisters.***\n    \n    *Do I have six sisters?* **[YES/NO]**, *I do.*\n    \n- ***I have a mother and father. They are my parents.***\n    \n    *Are my mother and father my parents?* **[YES/NO]**, *they are.*\n    \n- ***I have a grandmother. She is 84 years old.***\n    \n    *Is my grandmother 74 years old?* **[YES/NO]**, *she isn’t.*\n    \n- ***My oldest sister has one son.***\n    \n    *Does my sister have two sons?* **[YES/NO]**, *she doesn’t.*\n    \n- ***He is my nephew.***\n    \n    *Is my sister’s son my nephew?* **[YES/NO]**, *he is.*\n    \n- ***We live in Lima, Peru.***\n    \n    *Do I live in Lima?* **[YES/NO]**, *I do.*\n    \n- ***My mother has a brother.***\n    \n    *Does my mother have a sister?* **[YES/NO]**, *she doesn’t.*\n    \n- ***He is my uncle.***\n    \n    *Is my mother’s brother my uncle?* **[YES/NO]**, *he is.*\n    \n- ***My father has a sister.***\n    \n    *Does my father have a sister?* **[YES/NO]**, *he does.*\n    \n- ***And she is my aunt.***\n    \n    *Is my father’s sister called my uncle?* **[YES/NO]**, *she isn’t.*\n    \n- ***My aunt and uncle live outside the city.***\n    \n    *Do my aunt and uncle live in the city center?* **[YES/NO]**, *they don’t.*\n    \n- ***My aunt has one daughter.***\n    \n    *Does my aunt have a daughter?* **[YES/NO]**, *she does.*\n    \n- ***She is my cousin.***\n    \n    *Is my aunt’s daughter my cousin?* **[YES/NO]**, *she is.*\n    \n- ***I like to spend time with my family.***\n    \n    *Do I like to spend time with my family?* **[YES/NO]**, *I do.*\n    \n- ***I like to eat with my family.***\n    \n    *Do I like to eat with my family?* **[YES/NO]**, *I do.*\n    \n- ***My family likes to play soccer.***\n    \n    *Does my family like to play baseball?* **[YES/NO]**, *they don’t.*\n    \n- ***My brothers and sisters are good players.***\n    \n    *Do my brothers and sisters play well?* **[YES/NO]**, *they do.*\n    \n- ***My father and mother like to watch us play.***\n    \n    *Do my parents like to watch us play soccer?* **[YES/NO]**, *they do.*\n    \n- ***My parents are happy when we play well.***\n    \n    *Are my parents sad when we play well?* **[YES/NO]**, *they aren’t.*\n    \n\n---\n\n> ⚠️ IMPORTANTE\n> \n> \n> Solo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder **todas** las preguntas:\n> \n> ✅ de forma correcta · ✅ en voz alta · ✅ a tiempo · ✅ sin mirar el texto\n> \n\n---','[{\"label\":\"Video original en Drive\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/open?id=1jHb_SzqBr_ysBiRtsDUHfGWSQ92XN04y&usp=drive_fs\",\"description\":\"Enlace original exportado desde Notion.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter 1 - Story 2 - Family - Normal version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/family\\/chapter-1-story-2-family-normal-version.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter 1 - Story 2 - Family - Interactive version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/family\\/chapter-1-story-2-family-interactive-version.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/family.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/family/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/family/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/family/subtitle-en.vtt',1009,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:14','2026-05-08 08:04:14'),(117,2,'Traveling','traveling','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,3,'Escucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.','# ✈️Traveling\n\nSection 3 - Chapter 1\n\n---\n\n> 🎥 Video (Clase)\n> \n> \n> [https://drive.google.com/file/d/1r604W81b4J3aU-PsrnromGJe5YPhPjsv/view?usp=drive_link](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1r604W81b4J3aU-PsrnromGJe5YPhPjsv/view?usp=drive_link)\n> \n\n> 💡 Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n> \n\n---\n\n## ✅ 1) Escucha con traducción\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n🎧 **Audio:** *Normal version*\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+3+-+Traveling-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/traveling/chapter1-story3-traveling-normalversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n### 📖 Historia (con traducción)\n\n- ***I am traveling to Rome, Italy, today.***\n\n*Hoy viajo a Roma, Italia.*\n\n- ***I need several items to travel.***\n\n*Necesito varias cosas para viajar.*\n\n- ***I need a passport.***\n\n*Necesito un pasaporte.*\n\n- ***I can’t travel outside the country without a passport.***\n\n*No puedo viajar fuera del país sin pasaporte.*\n\n***I need money to travel.***\n\n*Necesito dinero para viajar.*\n\n***I want to buy souvenirs in Rome.***\n\n*Quiero comprar recuerdos en Roma.*\n\n***I can use a credit card to buy things too.***\n\n*También puedo utilizar una tarjeta de crédito para comprar cosas.*\n\n***I will stay at a hotel when I get to Rome.***\n\n*Me alojaré en un hotel cuando llegue a Roma.*\n\n***I use a suitcase and pack my clothes.***\n\n*Utilizo una maleta y preparo mi ropa.*\n\n***I will take my iPad and a book too.***\n\n*También llevaré mi iPad y un libro.*\n\n***My plane departs Mexico City at 11:00 am.***\n\n*Mi avión sale de Ciudad de México a las 11:00 am.*\n\n***My plane arrives in Rome at 10:00 pm.***\n\n*Mi avión llega a Roma a las 10:00 pm.*\n\n***I have to arrive at the airport early.***\n\n*Tengo que llegar pronto al aeropuerto.*\n\n***I take a taxi cab to the airport.***\n\n*Cojo un taxi hasta el aeropuerto.*\n\n***Security checks my luggage.***\n\n*Seguridad revisa mi equipaje.*\n\n***My plane takes off on time.***\n\n*Mi avión despega a la hora prevista.*\n\n***My flight to Rome is long.***\n\n*Mi vuelo a Roma es largo.*\n\n***I watch a movie on the plane.***\n\n*Veo una película en el avión.*\n\n***I am glad when the flight is over.***\n\n*Me alegro de que haya terminado.*\n\n***After I land, I check in at my hotel.***\n\n*Después de aterrizar, me registro en el hotel.*\n\n---\n\n## ✅ 2) Escucha sin traducción\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia **con los ojos cerrados**.\n\n🎧 **Audio:** *Normal version*\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+3+-+Traveling-+Normal+version (1).mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/traveling/chapter1-story3-traveling-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n***I am traveling to Rome, Italy, today.***\n\n***I need several items to travel.***\n\n***I need a passport.***\n\n***I can’t travel outside the country without a passport.***\n\n***I need money to travel.***\n\n***I want to buy souvenirs in Rome.***\n\n***I can use a credit card to buy things too.***\n\n***I will stay at a hotel when I get to Rome.***\n\n***I use a suitcase and pack my clothes.***\n\n***I will take my iPad and a book too.***\n\n***My plane departs Mexico City at 11:00 am.***\n\n***My plane arrives in Rome at 10:00 pm.***\n\n***I have to arrive at the airport early.***\n\n***I take a taxi cab to the airport.***\n\n***Security checks my luggage.***\n\n***My plane takes off on time.***\n\n***My flight to Rome is long.***\n\n***I watch a movie on the plane.***\n\n***I am glad when the flight is over.***\n\n***After I land, I check in at my hotel.***\n\n---\n\n## ✅ 3) Escucha y practica responder\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder **correctamente**, **a tiempo**, **en voz alta** y **con los ojos cerrados**.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+3+-+Traveling-+Interactive+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/traveling/chapter1-story3-traveling-interactiveversion.mp3)\n\n***I am traveling to Rome, Italy, today.***\n\n*Am I traveling to Rome today? [YES/NO], I am.*\n\n***I need several items to travel.***\n\n*Do I need only one item to travel? [YES/NO], I need several.*\n\n***I need a passport.***\n\n*Do I need a passport? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***I can’t travel outside the country without a passport.***\n\n*Can I travel outside the country without a passport? [YES/NO], I can’t.*\n\n***I need money to travel.***\n\n*Can I travel without money? [YES/NO], I can’t.*\n\n***I want to buy souvenirs in Rome.***\n\n*Do I want to buy souvenirs? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***I can use a credit card to buy things too.***\n\n*Can I use credit cards to buy things? [YES/NO], I can.*\n\n***I will stay at a hotel when I get to Rome.***\n\n*Will I stay at a resort when I get to Rome? [YES/NO], I will stay at a hotel.*\n\n***I use a suitcase and pack my clothes.***\n\n*Will I pack my clothes in a box? [YES/NO], I will use a suitcase.*\n\n***I will take my iPad and a book too.***\n\n*Will I take my book to Rome? [YES/NO], I will.*\n\n***My plane departs from Mexico City at 11:00 am.***\n\n*Does my plane depart at 9:00 am? [YES/NO], it doesn’t.*\n\n***My plane arrives in Rome at 10:00 pm.***\n\n*Does my plane arrive at 10:00 pm? [YES/NO], it does.*\n\n***I have to arrive at the airport early.***\n\n*Can I arrive at the airport late? [YES/NO], I can’t.*\n\n***I take a taxi cab to the airport.***\n\n*Do I ride my bike to the airport? [YES/NO], I don’t.*\n\n***My luggage is checked by security.***\n\n*Does the pilot check my luggage? [YES/NO], the pilot does not.*\n\n***My plane takes off on time.***\n\n*Does my plane take off late? [YES/NO], it takes off on time.*\n\n***My flight to Rome is long.***\n\n*Is the flight short? [YES/NO], it is a long flight.*\n\n***I watch a movie on the plane.***\n\n*Do I watch a movie on the flight? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***I am glad when the flight is over.***\n\n*Am I glad when the flight is over? [YES/NO], I am.*\n\n***After I land, I check in at my hotel.***\n\n*After I land, do I go and get pizza? [YES/NO], I check-in at the hotel.*\n\n**IMPORTANTE: \nSolo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder a todas las preguntas de forma correcta, en voz alta, a tiempo, y sin mirar el texto.**','[{\"label\":\"https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/file\\/d\\/1r604W81b4J3aU-PsrnromGJe5YPhPjsv\\/view?usp=drive_link\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/file\\/d\\/1r604W81b4J3aU-PsrnromGJe5YPhPjsv\\/view?usp=drive_link\",\"description\":\"Enlace externo importado desde las notas.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+3+-+Traveling-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/traveling\\/chapter1-story3-traveling-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+3+-+Traveling-+Normal+version (1).mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/traveling\\/chapter1-story3-traveling-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+3+-+Traveling-+Interactive+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/traveling\\/chapter1-story3-traveling-interactiveversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/traveling.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/traveling/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/traveling/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/traveling/subtitle-en.vtt',1196,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:14','2026-05-08 08:04:14'),(118,2,'Ordering Food','ordering-food','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,4,'Escucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.','# **Ordering Food**\n\n**Section 4 - Chapter 1**\n\n---\n\n> 🎥 Video (Clase)\n> \n> \n> [https://drive.google.com/file/d/10pQEM7fs9Mknx9AaXhFXJMsH9MuDt59j/view?usp=drive_link](https://drive.google.com/file/d/10pQEM7fs9Mknx9AaXhFXJMsH9MuDt59j/view?usp=drive_link)\n> \n\n> 💡 Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n> \n\n---\n\n## **1) Escucha con traducción**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+4+-+Ordering+food+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/ordering-food/chapter1-story4-orderingfood-normalversion.mp3)\n\n***I like to eat American food.***\n\n*Me gusta comer comida americana.*\n\n***I can order a hamburger meal.***\n\n*Puedo pedir una hamburguesa.*\n\n***The waitress asks, “What can I get for you today?”***\n\n*La camarera pregunta: \"¿Qué le sirvo hoy?\".*\n\n***I reply, “I’ll get the hamburger.”***\n\n*Yo respondo: \"La hamburguesa\".*\n\n***My hamburger can have toppings.***\n\n*Mi hamburguesa puede tener aderezos.*\n\n***I choose ketchup.***\n\n*Elijo ketchup.*\n\n***My hamburger can have vegetable toppings too.***\n\n*Mi hamburguesa también puede llevar ingredientes vegetales.*\n\n***The waitress asks, “Do you want lettuce, tomato, or onions?”***\n\n*La camarera pregunta: \"¿Quiere lechuga, tomate o cebolla?\".*\n\n***“Lettuce and tomato”, I answer.***\n\n*\"Lechuga y tomate\", respondo.*\n\n***I don’t like onions.***\n\n*No me gusta la cebolla.*\n\n***Cheese can be put on my hamburger.***\n\n*A mi hamburguesa le pueden poner queso.*\n\n***Then my hamburger is called a cheeseburger.***\n\n*Entonces mi hamburguesa se llama hamburguesa con queso.*\n\n***I like french fries to eat with my burger.***\n\n*Me gustan las patatas fritas para acompañar la hamburguesa.*\n\n***“Can I get an order of fries?”, I ask.***\n\n*\"¿Puedo pedir una porción de papas fritas?\", pregunto.*\n\n***I get a large order of french fries.***\n\n*Pido una porción grande de papas fritas.*\n\n***Last, the waitress asks what I want to drink.***\n\n*Por último, la camarera me pregunta qué quiero beber.*\n\n***“I want a small Coke,” I tell her.***\n\n*\"Quiero una Coca-Cola pequeña\", le digo.*\n\n***My girlfriend does not like hamburgers.***\n\n*A mi novia no le gustan las hamburguesas.*\n\n***I order a chicken sandwich for her.***\n\n*Pido un sándwich de pollo para ella.*\n\n***My girlfriend does not want french fries.***\n\n*Mi novia no quiere patatas fritas.*\n\n---\n\n## **2) Escucha sin traducción**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+4+-+Ordering+food+-+Normal+version (1).mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/ordering-food/chapter1-story4-orderingfood-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n***I like to eat American food.***\n\n***I can order a hamburger meal.***\n\n***The waitress asks, “What can I get for you today?”***\n\n***I reply, “I’ll get the hamburger.”***\n\n***My hamburger can have toppings.***\n\n***I choose ketchup.***\n\n***My hamburger can have vegetable toppings too.***\n\n***The waitress asks, “Do you want lettuce, tomato, or onions?”***\n\n***“Lettuce and tomato”, I answer.***\n\n***I don’t like onions.***\n\n***Cheese can be put on my hamburger.***\n\n***Then my hamburger is called a cheeseburger.***\n\n***I like french fries to eat with my burger.***\n\n***“Can I get an order of fries?”, I ask.***\n\n***I get a large order of french fries.***\n\n***Last, the waitress asks what I want to drink.***\n\n***“I want a small Coke,” I tell her.***\n\n***My girlfriend does not like hamburgers.***\n\n***I order a chicken sandwich for her.***\n\n***My girlfriend does not want french fries.***\n\n---\n\n# 3) **Escucha y practica responder**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas a tiempo, con los ojos cerrados.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+4+-+Ordering+food+-+Interactive+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/ordering-food/chapter1-story4-orderingfood-interactiveversion.mp3)\n\n***I like to eat American food.***\n\n*Do I like to eat American food? [YES/NO], I do.* \n\n***I will order a hamburger meal.***\n\n*Will I order a taco? [YES/NO], I won’t.*\n\n***The waitress asks, “What can I get for you today?”***\n\n*Does the waitress ask me to leave? [YES/NO], she doesn\'t.*\n\n***I reply, “I’ll get the hamburger.”***\n\n*Do I say I’ll get the soup? [YES/NO], I don’t.*\n\n***My hamburger can have toppings.***\n\n*Can my hamburger have toppings? [YES/NO], I can get toppings.*\n\n***I choose ketchup.***\n\n*Do I choose mustard? [YES/NO], I choose ketchup.*\n\n***The waitress asks, “Do you want lettuce, tomato, or onions?”***\n\n*Does the waitress ask if I want spinach? [YES/NO], she doesn’t.*\n\n***“Lettuce and tomato,” I answer.***\n\n*Do I say I want bacon? [YES/NO], I don’t.*\n\n***I don’t like onions.***\n\n*Do I like onions? [YES/NO], I don’t.*\n\n***Cheese can be put on my hamburger.***\n\n*Is cheese an option to put on my hamburger? [YES/NO], it is.*\n\n***Then my hamburger is called a cheeseburger.***\n\n*Does a cheeseburger have cheese on it? [YES/NO], it does.*\n\n***I like french fries to eat with my burger.***\n\n*Do I like to get fries with my burger? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***“Can I get an order of fries?” I ask.***\n\n*Do I ask for an order of beans? [YES/NO], I don’t.*\n\n***I get a large order of fries.***\n\n*Do I get a small order of fries? [YES/NO], I don’t.*\n\n***Last, the waitress asks what I want to drink.***\n\n*Does the waitress ask if I want dessert? [YES/NO], she asks what I want to drink.*\n\n***“I want a small Coke,” I tell her.***\n\n*Do I want a small Pepsi? [YES/NO], I don’t.*\n\n***My girlfriend does not like hamburgers.***\n\n*Does my girlfriend like hamburgers? [YES/NO], she does not.*\n\n***I order a chicken sandwich for her.***\n\n*Do I order her a taco? [YES/NO], I order a chicken sandwich.*\n\n***My girlfriend does not want french fries.***\n\n*Does my girlfriend want french fries? [YES/NO], she does not.*\n\n**IMPORTANTE: Solo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder a todas las preguntas de forma correcta, en voz alta, a tiempo, y sin mirar el texto.**','[{\"label\":\"https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/file\\/d\\/10pQEM7fs9Mknx9AaXhFXJMsH9MuDt59j\\/view?usp=drive_link\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/file\\/d\\/10pQEM7fs9Mknx9AaXhFXJMsH9MuDt59j\\/view?usp=drive_link\",\"description\":\"Enlace externo importado desde las notas.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+4+-+Ordering+food+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/ordering-food\\/chapter1-story4-orderingfood-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+4+-+Ordering+food+-+Normal+version (1).mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/ordering-food\\/chapter1-story4-orderingfood-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+4+-+Ordering+food+-+Interactive+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/ordering-food\\/chapter1-story4-orderingfood-interactiveversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/ordering-food.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/ordering-food/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/ordering-food/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/ordering-food/subtitle-en.vtt',1124,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:14','2026-05-08 08:04:14'),(119,2,'Shopping','shopping','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,5,'Escucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.','## 🛍️**Shopping**\n\n**Section 5, Chapter 1**\n\n---\n\n> 🎥 Video (Clase)\n> \n> \n> [https://drive.google.com/file/d/1PhVM80D3krIiVXjy0rK-cDbaGxPOfzpp/view?usp=drive_link](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1PhVM80D3krIiVXjy0rK-cDbaGxPOfzpp/view?usp=drive_link)\n> \n\n> 💡 Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n> \n\n---\n\n## **1. Escucha con traducción**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+5+-+Shopping+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/shopping/chapter1-story5-shopping-normalversion.mp3)\n\n***I buy groceries every week.***\n\n*Compro comida todas las semanas.*\n\n***I shop at the supermarket every Thursday.***\n\n*Voy al supermercado todos los jueves.*\n\n*(Error en audio: Dice \"I show up\" en lugar de \"I shop at\" )*\n\n***I make a list of the food I need.***\n\n*Hago una lista de los alimentos que necesito.*\n\n***This week, I need to buy many items.***\n\n*Esta semana necesito comprar muchos productos.*\n\n***At the store, I use a shopping cart to carry the food.***\n\n*En el supermercado, uso un carrito para llevar la comida.*\n\n***In the produce department, I get potatoes, apples, and carrots.***\n\n*En la sección de frutas y verduras compro patatas, manzanas y zanahorias.*\n\n***In the meat department, I get beef and chicken.***\n\n*En la sección de carne, compro ternera y pollo.*\n\n***Hmm, where is the bread aisle? I will ask.***\n\n*¿Dónde está el pasillo del pan? pregunto.*\n\n***“Excuse me sir, where can I find the bread?” – “Aisle five, sir.”***\n\n*\"Disculpe señor, ¿dónde puedo encontrar el pan?\" - \"Pasillo cinco, señor\".*\n\n***My dog needs food.***\n\n*Mi perro necesita comida.*\n\n***I get dog food.***\n\n*Consigo comida para perros.*\n\n***In the freezer section, there is ice cream. I buy vanilla ice cream.***\n\n*En la sección de congelados hay helados. Compro helado de vainilla.*\n\n***I remember that I need milk.***\n\n*Recuerdo que necesito leche.*\n\n***And, I also put eggs in the cart.***\n\n*Y también pongo huevos en el carro.*\n\n***I have put all I need into the cart. I go to the check-out counters.***\n\n*Pongo todo lo que necesito en el carro. Voy a la caja.*\n\n***I choose the self checkout counter.***\n\n*Elijo la caja automática.*\n\n***The kiosk allows me to look up the cost of the potatoes.***\n\n*La máquina me permite consultar el precio de las patatas.*\n\n***I use the scanner to add up the total cost of the food.***\n\n*Utilizo el escáner para sumar el precio total de los alimentos.*\n\n***I pay for the groceries.***\n\n*Pago la compra.*\n\n***I get a receipt and go home.***\n\n*Me dan un recibo y me voy a casa.*\n\n---\n\n# **2) Escucha sin traducción**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+5+-+Shopping+-+Normal+version (1).mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/shopping/chapter1-story5-shopping-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n***I buy groceries every week.***\n\n***I shop at the supermarket every Thursday.**(Error en audio: Dice \"I show up\" en lugar de \"I shop at\" )*\n\n***I make a list of the food I need.***\n\n***This week, I need to buy many items.***\n\n***At the store, I use a shopping cart to carry the food.***\n\n***In the produce department, I get potatoes, apples, and carrots.***\n\n***In the meat department, I get beef and chicken.***\n\n***Hmm, where is the bread aisle? I will ask.***\n\n***“Excuse me sir, where can I find the bread?” – “Aisle five, sir.”***\n\n***My dog needs food.***\n\n***I get dog food.***\n\n***In the freezer section, there is ice cream. I buy vanilla ice cream.***\n\n***I remember that I need milk.***\n\n***And, I also put eggs in the cart.***\n\n***I have put all I need into the cart. I go to the check-out counters.***\n\n***I choose the self checkout counter.***\n\n***The kiosk allows me to look up the cost of the potatoes.***\n\n***I use the scanner to add up the total cost of the food.***\n\n***I pay for the groceries.***\n\n***I get a receipt and go home.***\n\n---\n\n## **3) Escucha y practica responder**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas a tiempo, con los ojos cerrados.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+5+-+Shopping+-+Interactive+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/shopping/chapter1-story5-shopping-interactiveversion.mp3)\n\n***I buy groceries every week.***\n\n*Do I buy groceries every week? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***I shop at the supermarket every Thursday.***\n\n*Do I shop at the supermarket on Fridays? [YES/NO], I don’t. I shop on Thursdays.*\n\n***I make a list of the food I need.***\n\n*Before I shop, do I make a list of what I need? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***This week, I need to buy many items.***\n\n*This week, do I only need two items? [YES/NO], I need many.*\n\n***At the store, I use a shopping cart to carry the food.***\n\n*Do I use a shopping cart at the store? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***In the produce department, I get potatoes, apples, and carrots.***\n\n*Does the produce department have meat? [YES/NO], it has fruit and vegetables.*\n\n***In the meat department, I put beef and chicken in my cart.***\n\n*Do I get beef and lobster? [YES/NO], I do not.*\n\n***Hmm, where is the bread aisle? I will ask.***\n\n*Do I know where to find bread? [YES/NO], I do not.*\n\n***“Excuse me sir, where can I find the bread?”***\n\n***– “Aisle five, sir.”***\n\n*Is the bread in aisle four? [YES/NO], it is in aisle five.* \n\n***My dog needs food.***\n\n*Does my dog need food? [YES/NO], he does.*\n\n***I get dog food.***\n\n*Can I buy dog food at the supermarket? [YES/NO], I can.*\n\n***In the freezer section, there is ice cream. I get vanilla ice cream.***\n\n*Do I get vanilla ice cream? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***I remember that I need milk.***\n\n*Do I need juice? [YES/NO], I need milk.*\n\n***And, I also put eggs in the cart.***\n\n*Do I get eggs? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***I have put all I need into the cart. I go to the check-out counters.***\n\n*Do I leave the store when I have all my items? [YES/NO], I have to check out.*\n\n***I choose the self checkout counter.***\n\n*Do I choose the self checkout? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***The kiosk allows me to look up the cost of the potatoes.***\n\n*Does the kiosk tell me the cost of potatoes? [YES/NO], it does.*\n\n***I use the scanner to add up the total cost of the food.***\n\n*Do I use a calculator to add up the cost of the food? [YES/NO], I don’t.*\n\n***I pay for the groceries.***\n\n*Do I pay for the groceries after I scan them? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***I get a receipt and go home.***\n\n*Do I go to the park after I get the receipt? [YES/NO], I go home.*\n\n---\n\n**IMPORTANTE: Solo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder a todas las preguntas de forma correcta, en voz alta, a tiempo, y sin mirar el texto.**','[{\"label\":\"https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/file\\/d\\/1PhVM80D3krIiVXjy0rK-cDbaGxPOfzpp\\/view?usp=drive_link\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/file\\/d\\/1PhVM80D3krIiVXjy0rK-cDbaGxPOfzpp\\/view?usp=drive_link\",\"description\":\"Enlace externo importado desde las notas.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+5+-+Shopping+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/shopping\\/chapter1-story5-shopping-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+5+-+Shopping+-+Normal+version (1).mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/shopping\\/chapter1-story5-shopping-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+5+-+Shopping+-+Interactive+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/shopping\\/chapter1-story5-shopping-interactiveversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/shopping.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/shopping/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/shopping/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/shopping/subtitle-en.vtt',983,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:14','2026-05-08 08:04:14'),(120,2,'Body Parts','body-parts','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,7,'Escucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.','## **Body Parts**\n\n**Section 7, Chapter 1**\n\n---\n\n## **1)Escucha con traducción**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+6+-+Body+parts+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/body-parts/chapter1-story6-bodyparts-normalversion.mp3)\n\n***My body has many parts.***\n\n*Mi cuerpo tiene muchas partes.*\n\n***My head has two ears.***\n\n*Mi cabeza tiene dos orejas.*\n\n***I have two eyes and a nose on my face.***\n\nTengo dos ojos y una nariz en la cara.\n\n***I use my eyes to see a beautiful flower.***\n\n*Uso mis ojos para ver una hermosa flor.*\n\n***My ears hear my rap music.***\n\n*Mis oídos escuchan mi música rap.*\n\n***I taste my favorite food with my mouth.***\n\n*Con la boca pruebo mi comida favorita.*\n\n***My body has two arms.***\n\n*Mi cuerpo tiene dos brazos.*\n\n***My arms have hands.***\n\n*Mis brazos tienen manos.*\n\n***My arms and hands hold the person I love.***\n\n*Mis brazos y mis manos abrazan a la persona que amo.*\n\n***I use my fingers to play the piano.***\n\n*Toco el piano con los dedos.*\n\n***I have two legs.***\n\n*Tengo dos piernas.*\n\n***My legs are attached to my hips.***\n\n*Mis piernas están unidas a mis caderas.*\n\n***On my legs I have knees.***\n\n*En mis piernas tengo rodillas.*\n\n***At the end of each leg are my feet.***\n\n*Al final de cada pierna están mis pies.*\n\n***My feet are big.***\n\n*Mis pies son grandes.*\n\n***My feet have toes, and I have ten of them.***\n\n*Mis pies tienen dedos, y tengo diez.*\n\n***I use my legs and feet to walk, and run.***\n\n*Uso las piernas y los pies para andar y correr.*\n\n***When I am tired I sit on my butt.***\n\n*Cuando estoy cansado, me siento sobre mi trasero.*\n\n***I sometimes call my butt an ass.***\n\n*A veces llamo a mi trasero, \"culo\".*\n\n***But, my boyfriend calls my butt a booty!***\n\n*Pero ¡mi novio llama a mi trasero un culo!*\n\n---\n\n## **2. Escucha sin traducción**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+6+-+Body+parts+-+Normal+version (1).mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/body-parts/chapter1-story6-bodyparts-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n***My body has many parts.***\n\n***My head has two ears.***\n\n***I have two eyes and a nose on my face.***\n\n***I use my eyes to see a beautiful flower.***\n\n***My ears hear my rap music.***\n\n***I taste my favorite food with my mouth.***\n\n***My body has two arms.***\n\n***My arms have hands.***\n\n***My arms and hands hold the person I love.***\n\n***I use my fingers to play the piano.***\n\n***I have two legs.***\n\n***My legs are attached to my hips.***\n\n***On my legs I have knees.***\n\n***At the end of each leg are my feet.***\n\n***My feet are big.***\n\n***My feet have toes, and I have ten of them.***\n\n***I use my legs and feet to walk, and run.***\n\n***When I am tired I sit on my butt.***\n\n***I sometimes call my butt an ass.***\n\n***But, my boyfriend calls my butt a booty!***\n\n---\n\n## **3. Escucha y practica responder**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas a tiempo, con los ojos cerrados.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+6+-+Body+parts+-+Interactive+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/body-parts/chapter1-story6-bodyparts-interactiveversion.mp3)\n\n***My body has many parts.***\n\n*Does my body have many parts? [YES/NO], it does.*\n\n***My head has two ears.***\n\n*Do I have two ears? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***I have two eyes and a nose on my face.***\n\n*Do I have one eye? [YES/NO], I have two.*\n\n***I use my eyes to see a beautiful flower.***\n\n*Do I use my eyes to see a flower? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***My ears hear my rap music.***\n\n*Do my ears hear music? [YES/NO], they do.*\n\n***I taste my favorite food with my mouth.***\n\n*Do I taste with my mouth? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***My body has two arms.***\n\n*Does my body have three arms? [YES/NO], it has two.*\n\n***My arms have hands.***\n\n*Does my head have hands? [YES/NO], my arms have hands.*\n\n***My arms and hands hold the person I love.***\n\n*Do I hold a cat with my hands? [YES/NO], I don’t.*\n\n***I use my fingers to play the piano.***\n\n*Do my fingers play the flute? [YES/NO], I play the piano.*\n\n***I have two legs.***\n\n*Do I have two legs? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***My legs are attached to my hips.***\n\n*Are my legs attached to my arms? [YES/NO], they are attached to my hips.*\n\n***On my legs I have knees.***\n\n*Do my legs have knees? [YES/NO], they do.*\n\n***At the end of each leg are my feet.***\n\n*Do I have feet at the end of my legs? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***My feet are big.***\n\n*Are my feet small? [YES/NO], they are big.*\n\n***My feet have toes, and I have ten of them.***\n\n*Do I have ten toes? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***I use my legs and feet to walk, and run.***\n\n*Do I dance with my legs and feet? [YES/NO], I do not.*\n\n***When I am tired I sit on my butt.***\n\n*Do I sit on my butt? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***I sometimes call my butt an ass.***\n\n*Is my butt also called an ass? [YES/NO], it is.*\n\n***But, my boyfriend calls my butt a booty!***\n\n*Does my boyfriend call my butt a backside? [YES/NO], he calls it a booty.*\n\n---\n\n**IMPORTANTE: \nSolo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder a todas las preguntas de forma correcta, en voz alta, a tiempo, y sin mirar el texto.**','[{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+6+-+Body+parts+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/body-parts\\/chapter1-story6-bodyparts-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+6+-+Body+parts+-+Normal+version (1).mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/body-parts\\/chapter1-story6-bodyparts-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+6+-+Body+parts+-+Interactive+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/body-parts\\/chapter1-story6-bodyparts-interactiveversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/body-parts.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/body-parts/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/body-parts/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/body-parts/subtitle-en.vtt',961,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:14','2026-05-08 08:04:14'),(121,2,'Movies & TV','movies-tv','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,8,'Escucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.','## **Movies & TV** 📺\n\n**Section 8, Chapter 1**\n\n---\n\n## **1.)Escucha con traducción**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+7+-+Movies+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/movies-tv/chapter1-story7-movies-normalversion.mp3)\n\n***After work I like to watch TV.***\n\n*Después del trabajo me gusta ver la tele.*\n\n***I watch a TV series about a detective.***\n\n*Veo una serie de televisión sobre un detective.*\n\n***I watch this show every Tuesday night.***\n\n*Veo esta serie todos los martes por la noche.*\n\n***I also watch a TV series that is streamed.***\n\n*También veo una serie de televisión en directo.*\n\n***I can watch any episode any day I want.***\n\n*Puedo ver cualquier episodio el día que quiera.*\n\n***Sometimes I watch ten episodes in one day!***\n\n*A veces veo diez episodios en un día.*\n\n***I missed work because I “binge-watched\" a show.***\n\n*He faltado al trabajo porque me he \"maratoneado\" una serie.*\n\n***My friends and I also like to watch movies.***\n\n*A mis amigos y a mí también nos gusta ver películas.*\n\n***I like to go to the theater.***\n\n*A mí me gusta ir al teatro.*\n\n***I have to buy a ticket to see the movie.***\n\n*Tengo que comprar una entrada para ver la película.*\n\n***My friends go to see the movie with me.***\n\n*Mis amigos van a ver la película conmigo.*\n\n***I buy candy.***\n\n*Yo compro caramelos.*\n\n***But my friends buy popcorn and drinks.***\n\n*Pero mis amigos compran palomitas y bebidas.*\n\n***I see the movie on the huge screen.***\n\n*Veo la película en una pantalla enorme.*\n\n***I like to sit in the back seats of the theater.***\n\n*Me gusta sentarme en los asientos de atrás.*\n\n***My friends like to sit in the front seats.***\n\n*A mis amigos les gusta sentarse delante.*\n\n***I can watch movies at home too.***\n\n*También puedo ver películas en casa.*\n\n***But I like the theater better.***\n\n*Pero me gusta más el cine.*\n\n***The gigantic screen makes the movie exciting.***\n\n*La pantalla gigante hace que la película sea emocionante.*\n\n***And, I like the snacks too!***\n\n*Y también me gustan los aperitivos.*\n\n---\n\n## **2. Escucha sin traducción**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+7+-+Movies+-+Normal+version (1).mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/movies-tv/chapter1-story7-movies-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n***After work I like to watch TV.***\n\n***I watch a TV series about a detective.***\n\n***I watch this show every Tuesday night.***\n\n***I also watch a TV series that is streamed.***\n\n***I can watch any episode any day I want.***\n\n***Sometimes I watch ten episodes in one day!***\n\n***I missed work because I “binge-watched’ a show.***\n\n***My friends and I also like to watch movies.***\n\n***I like to go to the theater.***\n\n***I have to buy a ticket to see the movie.***\n\n***My friends go to see the movie with me.***\n\n***I buy candy.***\n\n***But my friends buy popcorn and drinks.***\n\n***I see the movie on the huge screen.***\n\n***I like to sit in the back seats of the theater.***\n\n***My friends like to sit in the front seats.***\n\n***I can watch movies at home too.***\n\n***But I like the theater better.***\n\n***The gigantic screen makes the movie exciting.***\n\n***And, I like the snacks too!***\n\n---\n\n## **3. Escucha y practica responder**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas a tiempo, con los ojos cerrados.\n\n[Chapter1-Story7-Movies-Interactiveversion.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/movies-tv/chapter1-story7-movies-interactiveversion.mp3)\n\n***After work I like to watch TV.***\n\n*Do I like to watch TV before work? [YES/NO], I don’t.*\n\n***I watch a TV series about a detective.***\n\n*Am I watching a TV series about a horse? [YES/NO], I am not.*\n\n***I watch this show every Tuesday night.***\n\n*Do I watch this show on Tuesday night? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***I also watch a TV series that is streamed.***\n\n*Do I watch another TV show that is streamed? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***I can watch any episode any day I want.***\n\n*Can I watch any episode any day? [YES/NO], I can.*\n\n***Sometimes I watch ten episodes in one day!***\n\n*Do I watch five episodes in a day? [YES/NO], I watch ten.*\n\n***I missed work because I “binge-watched’ a show.***\n\n*Did I miss work because I stayed home to watch a show? [YES/NO], I did.*\n\n***My friends and I also like to watch movies.***\n\n*Do my friends like to watch movies? [YES/NO],they do.*\n\n***I like to go to the theater.***\n\n*Do I like to go to the library? [YES/NO], I like to go to the theater.*\n\n***I have to buy a ticket to see the movie.***\n\n*Do I have to buy a ticket to see the movie? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***My friends go to see the movie with me.***\n\n*Do I go to the theater alone to see the movie? [YES/NO], I do not.*\n\n***I buy candy.***\n\n*Can you buy candy at the theater? [YES/NO], you can.*\n\n***But my friends buy popcorn and drinks.***\n\n*Do my friends buy popcorn? [YES/NO], they do.*\n\n***I see the movie on the huge screen.***\n\n*Do I see the movie on a huge screen? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***I like to sit in the back seats of the theater.***\n\n*Do I like to sit in the front of the theater? [YES/NO], I don\'t.*\n\n***My friends like to sit in the front seats.***\n\n*Do my friends like to sit in the front of the theater? [YES/NO], they do.*\n\n***I can watch movies at home too.***\n\n*Can I watch movies at home? [YES/NO], I can.*\n\n***But I like the theater better.***\n\n*Do I like the theater better? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***The gigantic screen makes the movie exciting.***\n\n*Is the small movie screen fun? [YES/NO], it isn’t.*\n\n***And, I like the snacks too!***\n\n*Do I like snacks? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n---\n\n**IMPORTANTE: \nSolo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder a todas las preguntas de forma correcta, en voz alta, a tiempo, y sin mirar el texto.**','[{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+7+-+Movies+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/movies-tv\\/chapter1-story7-movies-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+7+-+Movies+-+Normal+version (1).mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/movies-tv\\/chapter1-story7-movies-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter1-Story7-Movies-Interactiveversion.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/movies-tv\\/chapter1-story7-movies-interactiveversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/movies-tv.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/movies-tv/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/movies-tv/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/movies-tv/subtitle-en.vtt',810,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:14','2026-05-08 08:04:14'),(122,2,'Animals','animals','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,9,'Escucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.','## **Animals** 🐵\n\n**Section 9, Chapter 1**\n\n---\n\n> 🎥 Video (Clase)\n> \n> \n> https://drive.google.com/open?id=1jHb_SzqBr_ysBiRtsDUHfGWSQ92XN04y&usp=drive_fs\n> \n\n> 💡 Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n> \n\n---\n\n## **1. Escucha con traducción**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+8+-+Animals+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/animals/chapter1-story8-animals-normalversion.mp3)\n\n***My family and I like animals.***\n\n*A mi familia y a mí nos gustan los animales.*\n\n***I have a dog.***\n\n*Tengo un perro.*\n\n***My parents have two cats.***\n\n*Mis padres tienen dos gatos.*\n\n***My sister has three goldfish and a parakeet.***\n\n*Mi hermana tiene tres peces de dorados y un periquito.*\n\n***My family’s animals are pets.***\n\n*Los animales de mi familia son mascotas.*\n\n***In my country there are many wild animals.***\n\n*En mi país hay muchos animales salvajes.*\n\n***In the jungle, I have seen a jaguar.***\n\n*En la selva, he visto un jaguar.*\n\n***I once stepped on a large anaconda.***\n\n*Una vez me tropecé con una gran anaconda.*\n\n***That snake tried to eat me!***\n\n*Esa serpiente intentó comerme.*\n\n***My favorite wild animal is the toucan.***\n\n*Mi animal salvaje favorito es el tucán.*\n\n***I like this bird’s feathers.***\n\n*Me gustan las plumas de este pájaro.*\n\n***My friend has a farm.***\n\n*Mi amigo tiene una granja.*\n\n***I like his farm animals.***\n\n*Me gustan sus animales.*\n\n***I like eating the eggs laid by the chickens.***\n\n*Me gusta comer los huevos que ponen las gallinas.*\n\n***The cows give my family milk.***\n\n*Las vacas dan leche a mi familia.*\n\n***I like petting the alpaca.***\n\n*Me gusta acariciar a la alpaca.*\n\n***But once the alpaca spit on me.***\n\n*Pero una vez la alpaca me escupió.*\n\n***My country has lots of insects and bugs too.***\n\n*En mi país también hay muchos insectos y bichos.*\n\n***I do not like them.***\n\n*No me gustan.*\n\n***I am afraid of spiders.***\n\n*Me dan miedo las arañas.*\n\n***I would rather look at butterflies!***\n\n*Prefiero ver mariposas.*\n\n---\n\n## **2. Escucha sin traducción**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+8+-+Animals+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/animals/chapter1-story8-animals-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n***My family and I like animals.***\n\n***I have a dog.***\n\n***My parents have two cats.***\n\n***My sister has three goldfish and a parakeet.***\n\n***My family’s animals are pets.***\n\n***In my country there are many wild animals.***\n\n***In the jungle, I have seen a jaguar.***\n\n***I once stepped on a large anaconda.***\n\n***That snake tried to eat me!***\n\n***My favorite wild animal is the toucan.***\n\n***I like this bird’s feathers.***\n\n***My friend has a farm.***\n\n***I like his farm animals.***\n\n***I like eating the eggs laid by the chickens.***\n\n***The cows give my family milk.***\n\n***I like petting the alpaca.***\n\n***But once the alpaca spit on me.***\n\n***My country has lots of insects and bugs too.***\n\n***I do not like them.***\n\n***I am afraid of spiders.***\n\n***I would rather look at butterflies!***\n\n---\n\n## **3. Escucha y practica responder**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas a tiempo, con los ojos cerrados.\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+8+-+Animals+-+Interactive+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/animals/chapter1-story8-animals-interactiveversion.mp3)\n\n***My family and I like animals.***\n\n*Does my family like animals? [YES/NO], they do.*\n\n***I have a dog.***\n\n*Do I have a cat? [YES/NO], I don’t.*\n\n***My parents have two cats.***\n\n*Do my parents have four cats? [YES/NO], my parents have two.*\n\n***My sister has three goldfish and a parakeet.***\n\n*Does my sister have a dog? [YES/NO], she doesn’t.*\n\n***My family’s animals are pets.***\n\n*Does my family have pets? [YES/NO], they have pets.*\n\n***In my country there are many wild animals.***\n\n*Does my country have wild animals? [YES/NO], it does.*\n\n***In the jungle, I have seen a jaguar.***\n\n*Have I seen a bear in the jungle? [YES/NO], I have seen a jaguar.*\n\n***I once stepped on a large anaconda.***\n\n*Did I step on a monkey? [YES/NO], I didn’t.*\n\n***That snake tried to eat me!***\n\n*Did the snake try to eat me? [YES/NO], it did.*\n\n***My favorite wild animal is the toucan.***\n\n*Is my favorite wild animal the tree frog? [YES/NO], it isn’t.*\n\n***I like this bird’s feathers.***\n\n*Do I like the bird’s feathers? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n***My friend has a farm.***\n\n*Does my friend have a farm? [YES/NO], he does.*\n\n***I like his farm animals.***\n\n*Do I hate farm animals? [YES/NO], I like farm animals.*\n\n***I like eating the eggs laid by the chickens.***\n\n*Do the chickens lay eggs? [YES/NO], they do.*\n\n***The cows give my family milk.***\n\n*Do the cows give milk? [YES/NO], they do.*\n\n***I like petting the alpaca.***\n\n*Do I like petting the cows? [YES/NO], I don’t.*\n\n***But once the alpaca spit on me.***\n\n*Did the alpaca spit on me? [YES/NO], it did.*\n\n***My country has lots of insects and bugs too.***\n\n*Are there a large amount of bugs in my country? [YES/NO], there are.*\n\n***I do not like them.***\n\n*Do I love bugs? [YES/NO], I don\'t.*\n\n***I am afraid of spiders.***\n\n*Would I want to keep a spider as a pet? [YES/NO], I wouldn’t.*\n\n***I would rather look at butterflies!***\n\n*Do I like to look at butterflies? [YES/NO], I do.*\n\n---\n\n**IMPORTANTE: Solo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder a todas las preguntas de forma correcta, en voz alta, a tiempo, y sin mirar el texto.**','[{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+8+-+Animals+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/animals\\/chapter1-story8-animals-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+8+-+Animals+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/animals\\/chapter1-story8-animals-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+8+-+Animals+-+Interactive+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/animals\\/chapter1-story8-animals-interactiveversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/animals.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/animals/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/animals/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/animals/subtitle-en.vtt',995,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:14','2026-05-08 08:04:14'),(123,2,'Culture','culture','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,10,'Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.','## 🌍 Culture\n\n### Section 10 · Chapter 1\n\n**Tip:** Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n\n---\n\n> 🎥 Video (Clase)\n> \n> \n> https://drive.google.com/open?id=1jHb_SzqBr_ysBiRtsDUHfGWSQ92XN04y&usp=drive_fs\n> \n\n> 💡 Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n> \n\n---\n\n## 1️⃣ Escucha con traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n🎧 **Audio 1 – Escucha con traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+9+-+Culture+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/culture/chapter1-story9-culture-normalversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n**My country has an interesting culture.**\n\nMi país tiene una cultura interesante.\n\n**I celebrate holidays.**\n\nCelebro las fiestas.\n\n**My favorite is the Day of the Dead.**\n\nMi favorita es el Día de los Muertos.\n\n**I visit my family.**\n\nVisito a mi familia.\n\n**We remember those who have died.**\n\nRecordamos a los que han muerto.\n\n**I also like the Christmas holiday.**\n\nTambién me gusta la Navidad.\n\n**At Christmas I see poinsettia flowers.**\n\nEn Navidad veo flores de Pascua.\n\n**Mexico has beautiful art too.**\n\nMéxico también tiene un arte precioso.\n\n**I visit an art festival.**\n\nVisito un festival de arte.\n\n**I enjoy looking at the paintings.**\n\nMe gusta mirar los cuadros.\n\n**I like pictures with bright colors.**\n\nMe gustan los cuadros con colores vivos.\n\n**My girlfriend likes the jewelry.**\n\nA mi novia le gustan las joyas.\n\n**I buy her a silver bracelet.**\n\nLe compro una pulsera de plata.\n\n**My country has fun music too.**\n\nEn mi país también hay música divertida.\n\n**I like to listen to Mariachi music.**\n\nMe gusta escuchar música de mariachis.\n\n**Sometimes I dance too.**\n\nA veces también bailo.\n\n**I love to eat Mexican food.**\n\nMe encanta comer comida mexicana.\n\n**Tamales are my favorite.**\n\nLos tamales son mis favoritos.\n\n**But my girlfriend prefers tostadas.**\n\nPero mi novia prefiere las tostadas.\n\n**Art, music, food, and holidays are part of my culture.**\n\nEl arte, la música, la comida y las fiestas forman parte de mi cultura.\n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Escucha sin traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n🎧 **Audio 2 – Escucha sin traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+9+-+Culture+-+Normal+version (1).mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/culture/chapter1-story9-culture-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n---\n\nMy country has an interesting culture.\n\nI celebrate holidays.\n\nMy favorite is the Day of the Dead.\n\nI visit my family.\n\nWe remember those who have died.\n\nI also like the Christmas holiday.\n\nAt Christmas I see poinsettia flowers.\n\nMexico has beautiful art too.\n\nI visit an art festival.\n\nI enjoy looking at the paintings.\n\nI like pictures with bright colors.\n\nMy girlfriend likes the jewelry.\n\nI buy her a silver bracelet.\n\nMy country has fun music too.\n\nI like to listen to Mariachi music.\n\nSometimes I dance too.\n\nI love to eat Mexican food.\n\nTamales are my favorite.\n\nBut my girlfriend prefers tostadas.\n\nArt, music, food, and holidays are part of my culture.\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Escucha y practica responder\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas,\n\na tiempo, con los ojos cerrados y sin leer.\n\n🎧 **Audio 3 – Preguntas y respuestas**\n\n[Chapter1-Story9-Culture-InteractiveversionB.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/culture/chapter1-story9-culture-interactiveversionb.mp3)\n\n---\n\n**My country has an interesting culture.**\n\nDoes my country have a boring culture? **[YES / NO]**, it doesn\'t.\n\n**I celebrate holidays.**\n\nDo I celebrate holidays? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n\n**My favorite is the Day of the Dead.**\n\nIs Labor Day my favorite? **[YES / NO]**, it is not.\n\n**I visit my family.**\n\nDo I stay at home on the Day of the Dead? **[YES / NO]**, I don’t.\n\n**We remember those who have died.**\n\nDo I remember those who have died? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n\n**I also like the Christmas holiday.**\n\nDo I like the Christmas holiday? **[YES / NO]**, I do like Christmas.\n\n**At Christmas I see poinsettia flowers.**\n\nDo I see Christmas trees? **[YES / NO]**, I don’t.\n\n**Mexico has beautiful art too.**\n\nDoes Mexico have beautiful art? **[YES / NO]**, it does.\n\n**I visit an art festival.**\n\nDo I visit a museum? **[YES / NO]**, I don’t.\n\n**I enjoy looking at the paintings.**\n\nDo I hate looking at paintings? **[YES / NO]**, I enjoy looking at paintings.\n\n**I like pictures with bright colors.**\n\nDo I like pictures with dull colors? **[YES / NO]**, I don’t.\n\n**My girlfriend likes the jewelry.**\n\nDoes my girlfriend like jewelry? **[YES / NO]**, she does.\n\n**I buy her a silver bracelet.**\n\nDid I buy her a ring? **[YES / NO]**, I bought her a bracelet.\n\n**My country has fun music too.**\n\nIs the music in Mexico fun? **[YES / NO]**, it is.\n\n**I like to listen to Mariachi music.**\n\nDo I like to listen to rock music? **[YES / NO]**, I like Mariachi music.\n\n**Sometimes I dance too.**\n\nDo I dance? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n\n**I love to eat Mexican food.**\n\nDo I love to eat Italian food? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n\n**Tamales are my favorite.**\n\nAre tamales my favorite? **[YES / NO]**, they are.\n\n**But my girlfriend prefers tostadas.**\n\nDoes my girlfriend prefer tacos? **[YES / NO]**, she doesn’t.\n\n**Art, music, food, and holidays are part of my culture.**\n\nIs my work part of my culture? **[YES / NO]**, it isn’t.\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ IMPORTANTE\n\nSolo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder **todas las preguntas**:\n\n- En voz alta\n- A tiempo\n- Sin mirar el texto','[{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+9+-+Culture+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/culture\\/chapter1-story9-culture-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+9+-+Culture+-+Normal+version (1).mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/culture\\/chapter1-story9-culture-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter1-Story9-Culture-InteractiveversionB.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/culture\\/chapter1-story9-culture-interactiveversionb.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/culture.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/culture/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/culture/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/culture/subtitle-en.vtt',933,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:14','2026-05-08 08:04:14'),(124,2,'Exercise','exercise','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,11,'Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.','## 🏃 Exercise\n\n### Section 11 · Chapter 1\n\n**Tip:** Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n\n---\n\n> 🎥 Video (Clase)\n> \n> \n> https://drive.google.com/open?id=1jHb_SzqBr_ysBiRtsDUHfGWSQ92XN04y&usp=drive_fs\n> \n\n> 💡 Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n> \n\n---\n\n## 1️⃣ Escucha con traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n🎧 **Audio 1 – Escucha con traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+10+-+Exercise-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/exercise/chapter1-story10-exercise-normalversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n**Exercise is good for my body.**\n\nEl ejercicio es bueno para mi cuerpo.\n\n**Exercise makes me strong.**\n\nEl ejercicio me fortalece.\n\n**It keeps me healthy too.**\n\nTambién me mantiene sano.\n\n**I like to exercise five ways.**\n\nMe gusta hacer ejercicio de cinco maneras.\n\n**Jogging is my favorite.**\n\nMi favorito es trotar.\n\n**I jog in my neighborhood.**\n\nCorro por mi barrio.\n\n**I jog around my town.**\n\nCorro por mi ciudad.\n\n**I like to swim too.**\n\nTambién me gusta nadar.\n\n**I swim in a pool.**\n\nNado en la piscina.\n\n**But I also swim in the ocean.**\n\nPero también nado en el mar.\n\n**There is a gym in my town.**\n\nEn mi ciudad hay un gimnasio.\n\n**There I can lift weights.**\n\nAllí puedo levantar pesas.\n\n**Lifting weights makes muscles bigger.**\n\nLevantar pesas aumenta el tamaño de los músculos.\n\n**I can run on a treadmill there too.**\n\nTambién puedo correr en la caminadora.\n\n**My friend and I do yoga too.**\n\nMi amiga y yo también hacemos yoga.\n\n**Yoga helps me stay flexible.**\n\nEl yoga me ayuda a mantenerme flexible.\n\n**Stretching is good for my body.**\n\nLos estiramientos son buenos para mi cuerpo.\n\n**Walking on the beach is good exercise.**\n\nCaminar por la playa es un buen ejercicio.\n\n**I walk three kilometers.**\n\nYo camino tres kilómetros.\n\n**I enjoy different kinds of exercise.**\n\nMe gustan los distintos tipos de ejercicio.\n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Escucha sin traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n🎧 **Audio 2 – Escucha sin traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+10+-+Exercise-+Normal+version (1).mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/exercise/chapter1-story10-exercise-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n---\n\nExercise is good for my body.\n\nExercise makes me strong.\n\nIt keeps me healthy too.\n\nI like to exercise five ways.\n\nJogging is my favorite.\n\nI jog in my neighborhood.\n\nI jog around my town.\n\nI like to swim too.\n\nI swim in a pool.\n\nBut I also swim in the ocean.\n\nThere is a gym in my town.\n\nThere I can lift weights.\n\nLifting weights makes muscles bigger.\n\nI can run on a treadmill there too.\n\nMy friend and I do yoga too.\n\nYoga helps me stay flexible.\n\nStretching is good for my body.\n\nWalking on the beach is good exercise.\n\nI walk three kilometers.\n\nI enjoy different kinds of exercise.\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Escucha y practica responder\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas,\n\na tiempo, con los ojos cerrados y sin leer.\n\n🎧 **Audio 3 – Preguntas y respuestas**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+10+-+Exercise-+Interactive+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/exercise/chapter1-story10-exercise-interactiveversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n**Exercise is good for my body.**\n\nIs exercise good for my body? **[YES / NO]**, it is.\n\n**Exercise makes me strong.**\n\nDoes exercise make me weak? **[YES / NO]**, it makes me strong.\n\n**It keeps me healthy too.**\n\nDoes exercise make me healthy? **[YES / NO]**, it does.\n\n**I like to exercise five ways.**\n\nDo I like to exercise six ways? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n\n**Jogging is my favorite.**\n\nIs jogging my favorite? **[YES / NO]**, it is.\n\n**I jog in my neighborhood.**\n\nDo I jog in the park? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n\n**I jog around my town.**\n\nDo I jog in my town? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n\n**I like to swim too.**\n\nDo I hate swimming? **[YES / NO]**, I like swimming.\n\n**I swim in a pool.**\n\nDo I swim in a pool? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n\n**But I also swim in the ocean.**\n\nDo I also swim in the river? **[YES / NO]**, I swim in the ocean too.\n\n**There is a gym in my town.**\n\nIs there a gym in my town? **[YES / NO]**, there is.\n\n**There I can lift weights.**\n\nCan I lift weights there? **[YES / NO]**, I can.\n\n**Lifting weights makes muscles bigger.**\n\nDoes lifting weights make my muscles smaller? **[YES / NO]**, it does not.\n\n**I can run on a treadmill there too.**\n\nCan I run on a treadmill at the gym? **[YES / NO]**, I can.\n\n**My friend and I do yoga too.**\n\nDo I do yoga alone? **[YES / NO]**, I don’t.\n\n**Yoga helps me stay flexible.**\n\nDoes yoga help me be flexible? **[YES / NO]**, it does.\n\n**Stretching is good for my body.**\n\nIs stretching bad for my body? **[YES / NO]**, it is good for my body.\n\n**Walking on the beach is good exercise.**\n\nDo I walk in the forest? **[YES / NO]**, I walk on the beach.\n\n**I walk three kilometers.**\n\nDo I walk three kilometers? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n\n**I enjoy different kinds of exercise.**\n\nDo I like only one type of exercise? **[YES / NO]**, I like many.\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ IMPORTANTE\n\nSolo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder **todas las preguntas**:\n\n- En voz alta\n- A tiempo\n- Sin mirar el texto','[{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+10+-+Exercise-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/exercise\\/chapter1-story10-exercise-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+10+-+Exercise-+Normal+version (1).mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/exercise\\/chapter1-story10-exercise-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+10+-+Exercise-+Interactive+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/exercise\\/chapter1-story10-exercise-interactiveversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/exercise.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/exercise/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/exercise/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/exercise/subtitle-en.vtt',861,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:14','2026-05-08 08:04:14'),(125,2,'Las 15 Reglas de RAIO','las-15-reglas-de-raio','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,12,NULL,'## Las 15 Reglas de RAIO\n\n---\n\n![15 Rules of RAIO (JPG).jpg](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/las-15-reglas-de-raio/15-rules-of-raio-jpg.jpg)\n\n[15 Rules of RAIO (PDF).pdf](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/las-15-reglas-de-raio/15-rules-of-raio-pdf.pdf)\n\n.','[{\"label\":\"15 Rules of RAIO (JPG).jpg\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/las-15-reglas-de-raio\\/15-rules-of-raio-jpg.jpg\",\"description\":\"Imagen adjunta en la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"15 Rules of RAIO (PDF).pdf\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/las-15-reglas-de-raio\\/15-rules-of-raio-pdf.pdf\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/las-15-reglas-de-raio.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/las-15-reglas-de-raio/15-rules-of-raio-jpg.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/las-15-reglas-de-raio/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/las-15-reglas-de-raio/subtitle-en.vtt',1870,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:14','2026-05-08 08:04:14'),(126,2,'Hobbies','hobbies','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,13,'Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.','## 🎨 Hobbies\n\n### Section 13 · Chapter 1\n\n**Tip:** Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n\n---\n\n> 🎥 Video (Clase)\n> \n> \n> https://drive.google.com/open?id=1jHb_SzqBr_ysBiRtsDUHfGWSQ92XN04y&usp=drive_fs\n> \n\n## 1️⃣ Escucha con traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n🎧 **Audio 1 – Escucha con traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+11+-+Hobbies+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/hobbies/chapter1-story11-hobbies-normalversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n- **Having a hobby helps me relax.**\n    \n    Tener un hobby ayuda a relajarme.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I do my hobby in my free time.**\n    \n    Practico mi afición en mi tiempo libre.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like to be outside.**\n    \n    Me gusta estar al aire libre.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like to walk.**\n    \n    Me gusta caminar.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **So my hobby is hiking.**\n    \n    Así que mi afición es el senderismo.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My best friend likes to draw.**\n    \n    A mi mejor amiga le gusta dibujar.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like her pictures of animals.**\n    \n    Me gustan sus dibujos de animales.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I hung one of her drawings in my home.**\n    \n    He colgado uno de sus dibujos en mi casa.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My mother\'s hobby is sewing.**\n    \n    La afición de mi madre es coser.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **She sews clothes.**\n    \n    Ella cose ropa.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My father likes woodworking.**\n    \n    A mi padre le gusta trabajar la madera.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I have a birdhouse he made.**\n    \n    Tengo una pajarera que hizo él.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **The birdhouse is in my backyard.**\n    \n    La pajarera está en mi jardín.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My brother\'s hobby is playing video games.**\n    \n    La afición de mi hermano es jugar videojuegos.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like to play with him.**\n    \n    Me gusta jugar con él.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My neighbor’s hobby is skydiving.**\n    \n    El hobby de mi vecino es el paracaidismo.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I don\'t think I would like to skydive.**\n    \n    Creo que no me gustaría hacer paracaidismo.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My girlfriend\'s hobby is shopping.**\n    \n    La afición de mi novia es ir de compras.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I know she shops every day.**\n    \n    Sé que va de compras todos los días.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I told her she needs more money for her hobby!**\n    \n    Le he dicho que necesita más dinero para su afición.\n    \n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Escucha sin traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n🎧 **Audio 2 – Escucha sin traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+11+-+Hobbies+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/hobbies/chapter1-story11-hobbies-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n---\n\nHaving a hobby helps me relax.\n\nI do my hobby in my free time.\n\nI like to be outside.\n\nI like to walk.\n\nSo my hobby is hiking.\n\nMy best friend likes to draw.\n\nI like her pictures of animals.\n\nI hung one of her drawings in my home.\n\nMy mother’s hobby is sewing.\n\nShe sews clothes.\n\nMy father likes woodworking.\n\nI have a birdhouse he made.\n\nThe birdhouse is in my backyard.\n\nMy brother’s hobby is playing video games.\n\nI like to play with him.\n\nMy neighbor’s hobby is skydiving.\n\nI don\'t think I would like to skydive.\n\nMy girlfriend\'s hobby is shopping.\n\nI know she shops every day.\n\nI told her she needs more money for her hobby!\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Escucha y practica responder\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas,\n\na tiempo, con los ojos cerrados y sin leer.\n\n🎧 **Audio 3 – Preguntas y respuestas**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+11+-+Hobbies+-+Interactive+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/hobbies/chapter1-story11-hobbies-interactiveversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n- **Having a hobby helps me relax.**\n    \n    Do hobbies help me relax? **[YES / NO]**, they do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I do my hobby in my free time.**\n    \n    Do I do my hobby at work? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like to be outside.**\n    \n    Do I like to be indoors? **[YES / NO]**, I like being outside.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like to walk.**\n    \n    Do I like to play chess? **[YES / NO]**, I like to walk.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **So my hobby is hiking.**\n    \n    Is my hobby hiking? **[YES / NO]**, it is.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My best friend likes to draw.**\n    \n    Does my best friend like to paint? **[YES / NO]**, my friend likes to draw.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like her pictures of animals.**\n    \n    Do I like her pictures of animals? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I hung one of her drawings in my home.**\n    \n    Did I hang one of her drawings in my office? **[YES / NO]**, I didn’t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My mother\'s hobby is sewing.**\n    \n    Is sewing my mother\'s hobby? **[YES / NO]**, it is.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **She sews clothes.**\n    \n    Does she sew clothes? **[YES / NO]**, she does.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My father likes woodworking.**\n    \n    Is my father\'s hobby sailing? **[YES / NO]**, it is woodworking.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I have a birdhouse he made.**\n    \n    Did my father make a birdhouse? **[YES / NO]**, he did.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **The birdhouse is in my backyard.**\n    \n    Is the birdhouse in my sister\'s yard? **[YES / NO]**, it isn’t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My brother\'s hobby is playing video games.**\n    \n    Is my brother\'s hobby playing tennis? **[YES / NO]**, it isn’t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like to play with him.**\n    \n    Do I play games with him? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My neighbor\'s hobby is skydiving.**\n    \n    Is skydiving my neighbor\'s hobby? **[YES / NO]**, it is.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I don\'t think I would like to skydive.**\n    \n    Would I like skydiving? **[YES / NO]**, I would not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My girlfriend\'s hobby is shopping.**\n    \n    Does my girlfriend have a shopping hobby? **[YES / NO]**, she does.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I know she shops every day.**\n    \n    Does my girlfriend shop every day? **[YES / NO]**, she does.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I told her she needs more money for her hobby!**\n    \n    Did I tell her she needs more money for her hobby? **[YES / NO]**, I did.\n    \n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ IMPORTANTE\n\nSolo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder **todas las preguntas**:\n\n- En voz alta\n- A tiempo\n- Sin mirar el texto','[{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+11+-+Hobbies+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/hobbies\\/chapter1-story11-hobbies-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+11+-+Hobbies+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/hobbies\\/chapter1-story11-hobbies-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+11+-+Hobbies+-+Interactive+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/hobbies\\/chapter1-story11-hobbies-interactiveversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/hobbies.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/hobbies/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/hobbies/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/hobbies/subtitle-en.vtt',713,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:14','2026-05-08 08:04:14'),(127,2,'Holidays','holidays','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,14,'Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.','## 🎉 Holidays\n\n### Section 14 · Chapter 1\n\n**Tip:** Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n\n---\n\n> 🎥 Video (Clase)\n> \n> \n> https://drive.google.com/open?id=1jHb_SzqBr_ysBiRtsDUHfGWSQ92XN04y&usp=drive_fs\n> \n\n---\n\n## 1️⃣ Escucha con traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n🎧 **Audio 1 – Escucha con traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+12+-+Holidays-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/holidays/chapter1-story12-holidays-normalversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n- **Holidays are a fun time of year.**\n    \n    Las vacaciones son una época divertida del año.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I am off work on most holidays.**\n    \n    La mayoría de los días festivos no trabajo.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like Halloween.**\n    \n    Me gusta Halloween.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I wonder what kind of costume my sister will wear.**\n    \n    Me pregunto qué disfraz llevará mi hermana.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **“What are you wearing on Halloween?”**\n    \n    “¿Qué te vas a poner en Halloween?”\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My sister said she wants to be a cat.**\n    \n    Mi hermana dice que quiere ser un gato.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I want to wear a scary costume.**\n    \n    Yo quiero llevar un disfraz terrorífico.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I will dress as a zombie!**\n    \n    ¡Me disfrazaré de zombi!\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I plan to eat candy on Halloween.**\n    \n    Pienso comer caramelos en Halloween.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My family will cut faces on pumpkins.**\n    \n    Mi familia cortará caras en las calabazas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Christmas is another holiday I like.**\n    \n    La Navidad es otra fiesta que me gusta.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I will go to my parent’s house on Christmas Eve.**\n    \n    Iré a casa de mis padres en Nochebuena.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I want to buy my friend Joe a gift.**\n    \n    Quiero comprarle un regalo a mi amigo Joe.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I will ask Joe, “What would you like for Christmas?”**\n    \n    Le preguntaré a Joe: “¿Qué te gustaría para Navidad?”.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **“I want a new video game for my Xbox,” says Joe.**\n    \n    “Quiero un nuevo videojuego para mi Xbox”, dice Joe.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My mother wants a new sweater.**\n    \n    Mi madre quiere un suéter nuevo.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My dad wants new tools.**\n    \n    Mi padre quiere herramientas nuevas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I will see Nativity scenes in town.**\n    \n    Veré pesebres en la ciudad.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **But my American friends decorate Christmas trees.**\n    \n    Pero mis amigos americanos decoran árboles de Navidad.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I look forward to celebrating holidays.**\n    \n    Estoy deseando celebrar las fiestas.\n    \n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Escucha sin traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n🎧 **Audio 2 – Escucha sin traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+12+-+Holidays-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/holidays/chapter1-story12-holidays-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n---\n\nHolidays are a fun time of year.\n\nI am off work on most holidays.\n\nI like Halloween.\n\nI wonder what kind of costume my sister will wear.\n\n“What are you wearing on Halloween?”\n\nMy sister said she wants to be a cat.\n\nI want to wear a scary costume.\n\nI will dress as a zombie!\n\nI plan to eat candy on Halloween.\n\nMy family will cut faces on pumpkins.\n\nChristmas is another holiday I like.\n\nI will go to my parent’s house on Christmas Eve.\n\nI want to buy my friend Joe a gift.\n\nI will ask Joe, “What would you like for Christmas?”\n\n“I want a new video game for my Xbox,” says Joe.\n\nMy mother wants a new sweater.\n\nMy dad wants new tools.\n\nI will see Nativity scenes in town.\n\nBut my American friends decorate Christmas trees.\n\nI look forward to celebrating holidays.\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Escucha y practica responder\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas,\n\na tiempo, con los ojos cerrados y sin leer.\n\n🎧 **Audio 3 – Preguntas y respuestas**\n\n[Chapter1-Story12-Holidays-InteractiveversionB.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/holidays/chapter1-story12-holidays-interactiveversionb.mp3)\n\n---\n\n- **Holidays are a fun time of year.**\n    \n    Do I think holidays are fun? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I am off work on most holidays.**\n    \n    Do I work on holidays? **[YES / NO]**, I don\'t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like Halloween.**\n    \n    Do I dislike Halloween? **[YES / NO]**, I like Halloween.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I wonder what kind of costume my sister will wear.**\n    \n    Do I know what my sister will wear? **[YES / NO]**, I don’t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **“What are you wearing on Halloween?”**\n    \n    Did I ask her what she would wear for Labor Day? **[YES / NO]**, I did not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My sister said she wants to be a cat.**\n    \n    Does my sister want to be a cat? **[YES / NO]**, she does.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I want to wear a scary costume.**\n    \n    Do I want to wear a funny costume? **[YES / NO]**, I don\'t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I will dress as a zombie!**\n    \n    Am I going to dress up as a zombie? **[YES / NO]**, I am.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I plan to eat candy on Halloween.**\n    \n    Am I planning on eating vegetables on Halloween? **[YES / NO]**, I am not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My family will cut faces on pumpkins.**\n    \n    Will my family cut faces on pumpkins? **[YES / NO]**, they will.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Christmas is another holiday I like.**\n    \n    Do I like Christmas? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I will go to my parent\'s house on Christmas Eve.**\n    \n    Will I visit my family on Christmas Day? **[YES / NO]**, I will.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I want to buy my friend Joe a gift.**\n    \n    Do I want to buy Chris a gift? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I will ask Joe, “What would you like for Christmas?”**\n    \n    Will I ask Joe what he wants? **[YES / NO]**, I will.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **“I want a new video game for my Xbox,” says Joe.**\n    \n    Does Joe want a video game? **[YES / NO]**, he does.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My mother wants a new sweater.**\n    \n    Does my mother want a new coat? **[YES / NO]**, she does not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My dad wants new tools.**\n    \n    Does my dad want new shoes? **[YES / NO]**, he does not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I will see Nativity scenes in town.**\n    \n    Will I see Nativity scenes in town? **[YES / NO]**, I will.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **But my American friends decorate Christmas trees.**\n    \n    Do my American friends decorate Christmas trees? **[YES / NO]**, they do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I look forward to celebrating holidays.**\n    \n    Do I look forward to celebrating? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ IMPORTANTE\n\nSolo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder **todas las preguntas**:\n\n- En voz alta\n- A tiempo\n- Sin mirar el texto\n\nCuando quieras, envíame la **siguiente sección** y seguimos con el mismo formato 👌📘','[{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+12+-+Holidays-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/holidays\\/chapter1-story12-holidays-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+12+-+Holidays-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/holidays\\/chapter1-story12-holidays-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter1-Story12-Holidays-InteractiveversionB.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/holidays\\/chapter1-story12-holidays-interactiveversionb.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/holidays.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/holidays/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/holidays/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/holidays/subtitle-en.vtt',800,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:15','2026-05-08 08:04:15'),(128,2,'Hometown','hometown','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,15,'Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.','## 🏡 Hometown\n\n### Section 15 · Chapter 1\n\n**Tip:** Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n\n---\n\n## 1️⃣ Escucha con traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n🎧 **Audio 1 – Escucha con traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+13+-+Hometown+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/hometown/chapter1-story13-hometown-normalversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n- **I live in Mexico.**\n    \n    Vivo en México.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I live in the state of Durango.**\n    \n    Vivo en el estado de Durango.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My hometown is east of Mazatlan.**\n    \n    Mi pueblo está al este de Mazatlán.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **The name of my town is Lerdo, Durango.**\n    \n    El nombre de mi pueblo es Lerdo, Durango.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My hometown is small.**\n    \n    Mi pueblo natal es pequeño.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like the warm weather in my hometown.**\n    \n    Me gusta el clima cálido de mi ciudad natal.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I can work and play outside all year.**\n    \n    Puedo trabajar y jugar al aire libre todo el año.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I hike on trails near my town.**\n    \n    Hago montañismo por senderos cercanos a mi ciudad.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My friends and I go to Victoria Park.**\n    \n    Mis amigos y yo vamos al Parque Victoria.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My town is well-known for its ice cream.**\n    \n    Mi pueblo es conocido por sus helados.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **There are dairy farms near my town.**\n    \n    Hay granjas lecheras cerca de mi pueblo.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I went to school in Lerdo.**\n    \n    Yo fui al colegio en Lerdo.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My school was near my home.**\n    \n    Mi colegio estaba cerca de mi casa.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I live in a yellow house.**\n    \n    Vivo en una casa amarilla.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My house has two bedrooms.**\n    \n    Mi casa tiene dos dormitorios.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I work downtown.**\n    \n    Trabajo en el centro.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My town has many shops.**\n    \n    Mi ciudad tiene muchas tiendas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I work in a jewelry store.**\n    \n    Trabajo en una joyería.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My town has art galleries too.**\n    \n    En mi pueblo también hay galerías de arte.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I think you will like my hometown.**\n    \n    Creo que te gustará mi ciudad.\n    \n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Escucha sin traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n🎧 **Audio 2 – Escucha sin traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+13+-+Hometown+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/hometown/chapter1-story13-hometown-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n---\n\nI live in Mexico.\n\nI live in the state of Durango.\n\nMy hometown is east of Mazatlan.\n\nThe name of my town is Lerdo, Durango.\n\nMy hometown is small.\n\nI like the warm weather in my hometown.\n\nI can work and play outside all year.\n\nI hike on trails near my town.\n\nMy friends and I go to Victoria Park.\n\nMy town is well-known for its ice cream.\n\nThere are dairy farms near my town.\n\nI went to school in Lerdo.\n\nMy school was near my home.\n\nI live in a yellow house.\n\nMy house has two bedrooms.\n\nI work downtown.\n\nMy town has many shops.\n\nI work in a jewelry store.\n\nMy town has art galleries too.\n\nI think you will like my hometown.\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Escucha y practica responder\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas,\n\na tiempo, con los ojos cerrados y sin leer.\n\n🎧 **Audio 3 – Preguntas y respuestas**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+13+-+Hometown+-+Interactive+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/hometown/chapter1-story13-hometown-interactiveversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n- **I live in Mexico.**\n    \n    Do I live in Peru? **[YES / NO]**, I live in Mexico.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I live in the state of Durango.**\n    \n    Do I live in the state of Durango? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My hometown is east of Mazatlan.**\n    \n    Is my hometown west of Mazatlan? **[YES / NO]**, it is not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **The name of my town is Lerdo, Durango.**\n    \n    Is the name of my town Lerdo? **[YES / NO]**, it is.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My hometown is small.**\n    \n    Is my hometown large? **[YES / NO]**, it is a small town.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like the warm weather in my hometown.**\n    \n    Is the weather cold in my hometown? **[YES / NO]**, the weather is warm.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I can work and play outside all year.**\n    \n    Can I work and play outside all year? **[YES / NO]**, I can.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I hike on trails near my town.**\n    \n    Do I hike on trails? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My friends and I go to Victoria Park.**\n    \n    Do my friends and I go to Winton Park? **[YES / NO]**, we don\'t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My town is well-known for its ice cream.**\n    \n    Is my town known for having ice cream? **[YES / NO]**, it is.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **There are dairy farms near my town.**\n    \n    Are there dairy farms nearby? **[YES / NO]**, there are.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I went to school in Lerdo.**\n    \n    Did I go to school in Mexico City? **[YES / NO]**, I went to school in Lerdo.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My school was near my home.**\n    \n    Did I live near my school? **[YES / NO]**, I did.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I live in a yellow house.**\n    \n    Is my house gray? **[YES / NO]**, it is yellow.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My house has two bedrooms.**\n    \n    Does my house have two bedrooms? **[YES / NO]**, it does.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I work downtown.**\n    \n    Do I work on a farm? **[YES / NO]**, I work downtown.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My town has many shops.**\n    \n    Does my town have many shops? **[YES / NO]**, it does.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I work in a jewelry store.**\n    \n    Do I work in a bookstore? **[YES / NO]**, I work in a jewelry store.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My town has art galleries too.**\n    \n    Does my town have art galleries? **[YES / NO]**, it does.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I think you will like my hometown.**\n    \n    Do I think you will like my hometown? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ IMPORTANTE\n\nSolo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder **todas las preguntas**:\n\n- En voz alta\n- A tiempo\n- Sin mirar el texto','[{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+13+-+Hometown+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/hometown\\/chapter1-story13-hometown-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+13+-+Hometown+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/hometown\\/chapter1-story13-hometown-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+13+-+Hometown+-+Interactive+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/hometown\\/chapter1-story13-hometown-interactiveversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/hometown.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/hometown/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/hometown/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/hometown/subtitle-en.vtt',705,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:15','2026-05-08 08:04:15'),(129,2,'Work','work','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,16,'Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.','## 💼 Work\n\n### Section 16 · Chapter 1\n\n**Tip:** Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n\n---\n\n## 1️⃣ Escucha con traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n🎧 **Audio 1 – Escucha con traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+14+-+Work-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/work/chapter1-story14-work-normalversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n- **I must be at work at 8:00 am.**\n    \n    Debo estar en el trabajo a las 8 de la mañana.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I have many bills, so I have to work.**\n    \n    Tengo muchas facturas, así que tengo que trabajar.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My shift is from 8:00 am to 5:00 pm.**\n    \n    Mi turno es de 8 de la mañana a 5 de la tarde.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I work at a call center.**\n    \n    Trabajo en un centro de llamadas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Customers call me when they have questions.**\n    \n    Los clientes me llaman cuando tienen preguntas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **When the phone rings, I say, “How may I help you today?”**\n    \n    Cuando suena el teléfono, digo: “¿En qué puedo ayudarle hoy?”.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I answer questions about their payments.**\n    \n    Respondo a preguntas sobre sus pagos.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I also solve problems.**\n    \n    También resuelvo problemas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I help customers fix their computers.**\n    \n    Ayudo a los clientes a arreglar sus ordenadores.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I tell them to check to see if it\'s plugged in.**\n    \n    Les digo que comprueben si está enchufado.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Then I ask them to restart.**\n    \n    Luego les pido que lo reinicien.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Sometimes I can’t fix the problem.**\n    \n    A veces no puedo solucionar el problema.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Then I call my supervisor.**\n    \n    Entonces llamo a mi supervisor.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My supervisor is very helpful.**\n    \n    Mi supervisor es muy servicial.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I answer questions all morning.**\n    \n    Respondo preguntas toda la mañana.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Then I take a break for lunch.**\n    \n    Luego hago una pausa para comer.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **After I eat, I begin answering calls again.**\n    \n    Después de comer, vuelvo a responder a las llamadas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I work weekdays.**\n    \n    Trabajo entre semana.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **On Friday, I get paid.**\n    \n    El viernes me pagan.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I am glad I can work and earn money.**\n    \n    Me alegro de poder trabajar y ganar dinero.\n    \n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Escucha sin traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n🎧 **Audio 2 – Escucha sin traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+14+-+Work-+Normal+version (1).mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/work/chapter1-story14-work-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n---\n\nI must be at work at 8:00 am.\n\nI have many bills, so I have to work.\n\nMy shift is from 8:00 am to 5:00 pm.\n\nI work at a call center.\n\nCustomers call me when they have questions.\n\nWhen the phone rings, I say, “How may I help you today?”\n\nI answer questions about their payments.\n\nI also solve problems.\n\nI help customers fix their computers.\n\nI tell them to check to see if it\'s plugged in.\n\nThen I ask them to restart.\n\nSometimes I can\'t fix the problem.\n\nThen I call my supervisor.\n\nMy supervisor is very helpful.\n\nI answer questions all morning.\n\nThen I take a break for lunch.\n\nAfter I eat, I begin answering calls again.\n\nI work weekdays.\n\nOn Friday, I get paid.\n\nI am glad I can work and earn money.\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Escucha y practica responder\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas,\n\na tiempo, con los ojos cerrados y sin leer.\n\n🎧 **Audio 3 – Preguntas y respuestas**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+14+-+Work-+Interactive+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/work/chapter1-story14-work-interactiveversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n- **I must be at work at 8:00 am.**\n    \n    Do I have to be at work at 8:00 am? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I have many bills, so I have to work.**\n    \n    Do I work so I can pay my bills? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My shift is from 8:00 am to 5:00 pm.**\n    \n    Is my work shift over at 4:00 pm? **[YES / NO]**, I work until 5:00.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I work at a call center.**\n    \n    Do I work at a factory? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Customers call me when they have questions.**\n    \n    Do customers call me when they have a question? **[YES / NO]**, they do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **When the phone rings, I say, “How may I help you today?”**\n    \n    When the phone rings, do I say, “I can\'t help you now”? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I answer questions about their payments.**\n    \n    Do I answer questions about their payments? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I also solve problems.**\n    \n    Do I solve their problems? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I help customers fix their computers.**\n    \n    Do I help customers fix their phones? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I tell them to check to see if it\'s plugged in.**\n    \n    Do I tell them to turn their computers on? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Then I ask them to restart.**\n    \n    Do I ask them to restart their computer? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Sometimes I can\'t fix the problem.**\n    \n    Do I fix every problem? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Then I call my supervisor.**\n    \n    Do I call my co-worker when I can\'t fix a problem? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My supervisor is very helpful.**\n    \n    Is my supervisor helpful? **[YES / NO]**, she is.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I answer questions all morning.**\n    \n    Do I answer questions all morning? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Then I take a break for lunch.**\n    \n    Do I take a break and play games? **[YES / NO]**, I eat lunch.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **After I eat, I begin answering calls again.**\n    \n    After lunch, do I go home? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I work weekdays.**\n    \n    Do I work on Saturday? **[YES / NO]**, I work weekdays.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **On Friday, I get paid.**\n    \n    Do I get paid on Thursday? **[YES / NO]**, I get paid on Friday.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I am glad I can work and earn money.**\n    \n    Am I sad that I can work? **[YES / NO]**, I am glad.\n    \n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ IMPORTANTE\n\nSolo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder **todas las preguntas**:\n\n- En voz alta\n- A tiempo\n- Sin mirar el texto','[{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+14+-+Work-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/work\\/chapter1-story14-work-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+14+-+Work-+Normal+version (1).mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/work\\/chapter1-story14-work-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+14+-+Work-+Interactive+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/work\\/chapter1-story14-work-interactiveversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/work.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/work/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/work/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/work/subtitle-en.vtt',996,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:15','2026-05-08 08:04:15'),(130,2,'Love','love','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,17,'Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.','## ❤️ Love\n\n### Section 17 · Chapter 1\n\n**Tip:** Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n\n---\n\n## 1️⃣ Escucha con traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n🎧 **Audio 1 – Escucha con traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+15+-+Love+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/love/chapter1-story15-love-normalversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n- **I love many people.**\n    \n    Quiero a mucha gente.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I love my family.**\n    \n    Quiero a mi familia.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I love my mom because she takes care of everyone.**\n    \n    Quiero a mi madre porque cuida de todos.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I love my dad. He helps me build things.**\n    \n    Quiero a mi padre. Me ayuda a construir cosas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I love my siblings. We play games.**\n    \n    Quiero a mis hermanos. Nosotros jugamos.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My family cares for each other.**\n    \n    Mi familia se preocupa por los demás.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I love my girlfriend.**\n    \n    Quiero a mi novia.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My love for her is different.**\n    \n    Mi amor por ella es diferente.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My love for her is romantic love.**\n    \n    Mi amor por ella es amor romántico.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I want to go out on dates.**\n    \n    Quiero salir con ella.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Because I love her I want to kiss her.**\n    \n    Porque la quiero, quiero besarla.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like holding her too.**\n    \n    También me gusta abrazarla.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I love my friends.**\n    \n    Yo quiero a mis amigos.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My love for my friends is not romantic love.**\n    \n    Mi amor por mis amigos no es amor romántico.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My friends help me.**\n    \n    Mis amigos me ayudan.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I help them when they need help too.**\n    \n    Yo también les ayudo cuando lo necesitan.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **But I do not want to kiss my friends!**\n    \n    Pero no quiero besar a mis amigos.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I even love my dog.**\n    \n    Incluso quiero a mi perro.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My dog loves me too. He licks my face.**\n    \n    Mi perro también me quiere. Me lame la cara.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I guess my dog likes to kiss me!**\n    \n    Supongo que a mi perro le gusta besarme.\n    \n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Escucha sin traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n🎧 **Audio 2 – Escucha sin traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+15+-+Love+-+Normal+version (1).mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/love/chapter1-story15-love-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n---\n\nI love many people.\n\nI love my family.\n\nI love my mom because she takes care of everyone.\n\nI love my dad. He helps me build things.\n\nI love my siblings. We play games.\n\nMy family cares for each other.\n\nI love my girlfriend.\n\nMy love for her is different.\n\nMy love for her is romantic love.\n\nI want to go out on dates.\n\nBecause I love her I want to kiss her.\n\nI like holding her too.\n\nI love my friends.\n\nMy love for my friends is not romantic love.\n\nMy friends help me.\n\nI help them when they need help too.\n\nBut I do not want to kiss my friends!\n\nI even love my dog.\n\nMy dog loves me too. He licks my face.\n\nI guess my dog likes to kiss me!\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Escucha y practica responder\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas,\n\na tiempo, con los ojos cerrados y sin mirar el texto.\n\n🎧 **Audio 3 – Preguntas y respuestas**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+15+-+Love+-+Interactive+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/love/chapter1-story15-love-interactiveversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n- **I love many people.**\n    \n    Do I only love two people? **[YES / NO]**, I love many.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I love my family.**\n    \n    Do I love my family? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I love my mom because she takes care of everyone.**\n    \n    Do I love my mom because she is funny? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I love my dad. He helps me build things.**\n    \n    Does my dad help me build things? **[YES / NO]**, he does.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I love my siblings. We play games.**\n    \n    Do I hate my siblings? **[YES / NO]**, I do not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My family cares for each other.**\n    \n    Does my family care for each other? **[YES / NO]**, they do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I love my girlfriend.**\n    \n    Do I like my girlfriend? **[YES / NO]**, I love her.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My love for her is different.**\n    \n    Is my love for her the same as family love? **[YES / NO]**, it is different.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My love for her is romantic love.**\n    \n    Is my love for her romantic? **[YES / NO]**, it is.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I take her on dates.**\n    \n    Do I take my girlfriend on dates? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Because I love her I want to kiss her.**\n    \n    Do I want to kiss her? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I like holding her too.**\n    \n    Do I like holding my girlfriend? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I love my friends.**\n    \n    Do I love my friends? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My love for my friends is not romantic love.**\n    \n    Is my love for my friends romantic love? **[YES / NO]**, it is not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My friends help me.**\n    \n    Do my friends ignore me if I need help? **[YES / NO]**, they help me.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I help them when they need help too.**\n    \n    Do I help my friends? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **But I do not want to kiss my friends!**\n    \n    Do I want to kiss my friends? **[YES / NO]**, I don\'t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I even love my dog.**\n    \n    Do I love my dog? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My dog loves me too. He licks my face.**\n    \n    Does my dog bite my face? **[YES / NO]**, he licks my face.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I guess my dog likes to kiss me!**\n    \n    Does my dog like to kiss me? **[YES / NO]**, it does.\n    \n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ IMPORTANTE\n\nSolo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder **todas las preguntas**:\n\n- En voz alta\n- A tiempo\n- Sin mirar el texto','[{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+15+-+Love+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/love\\/chapter1-story15-love-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+15+-+Love+-+Normal+version (1).mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/love\\/chapter1-story15-love-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+15+-+Love+-+Interactive+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/love\\/chapter1-story15-love-interactiveversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/love.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/love/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/love/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/love/subtitle-en.vtt',984,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:15','2026-05-08 08:04:15'),(131,2,'Household Items','household-items','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,19,'Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.','## 🏠 Household Items\n\n### Section 19 · Chapter 1\n\n**Tip:** Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n\n---\n\n## 1️⃣ Escucha con traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n🎧 **Audio 1 – Escucha con traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+16+-+Household+Items+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/household-items/chapter1-story16-householditems-normalversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n- **I rented my first apartment!**\n    \n    ¡He alquilado mi primer apartamento!\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My roommate, Bill and I need household items.**\n    \n    Mi compañero de piso, Bill, y yo necesitamos artículos para el hogar.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I need a bed.**\n    \n    Necesito una cama.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I also need a table and chairs for the kitchen.**\n    \n    También necesito una mesa y sillas para la cocina.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Bill has a couch.**\n    \n    Bill tiene un sofá.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I think we need a chair for the living room.**\n    \n    Creo que necesitamos una silla para la sala.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I need a large screen TV.**\n    \n    Necesito un televisor de pantalla grande.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Bill disagrees.**\n    \n    Bill no está de acuerdo.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I need things to cook with too.**\n    \n    Yo también necesito cosas para cocinar.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **But Bill already has some.**\n    \n    Pero Bill ya tiene algunas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **“Do you have pots and pans?” I ask.**\n    \n    \"¿Tienes ollas y sartenes?\" le pregunto.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **“Yes. But I don\'t have any dishes.” Bill replies.**\n    \n    \"Sí, pero no tengo platos\", responde Bill.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **At the home store, I buy dishes.**\n    \n    En la tienda del hogar, compro platos.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I ask Bill to buy forks and spoons.**\n    \n    Le pido a Bill que compre tenedores y cucharas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I don\'t have bed sheets and towels.**\n    \n    No tengo sábanas ni toallas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Bill needs blankets.**\n    \n    Bill necesita mantas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Bill and I go to another store.**\n    \n    Bill y yo vamos a otra tienda.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **There I buy bed sheets and three towels.**\n    \n    Allí compro sábanas y tres toallas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I have very little money left.**\n    \n    Me queda muy poco dinero.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **And, I still don’t have a bed!**\n    \n    ¡Y todavía no tengo cama!\n    \n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Escucha sin traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n🎧 **Audio 2 – Escucha sin traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+16+-+Household+Items+-+Normal+version (1).mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/household-items/chapter1-story16-householditems-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n---\n\nI rented my first apartment!\n\nMy roommate, Bill and I need household items.\n\nI need a bed.\n\nI also need a table and chairs for the kitchen.\n\nBill has a couch.\n\nI think we need a chair for the living room.\n\nI need a large screen TV.\n\nBill disagrees.\n\nI need things to cook with too.\n\nBut Bill already has some.\n\n“Do you have pots and pans?” I ask.\n\n“Yes. But I don’t have any dishes.” Bill replies.\n\nAt the home store, I buy dishes.\n\nI ask Bill to buy forks and spoons.\n\nI don\'t have bed sheets and towels.\n\nBill needs blankets.\n\nBill and I go to another store.\n\nThere I buy bed sheets and three towels.\n\nI have very little money left.\n\nAnd, I still don’t have a bed!\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Escucha y practica responder\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas,\n\na tiempo, con los ojos cerrados y sin mirar el texto.\n\n🎧 **Audio 3 – Preguntas y respuestas**\n\n[https://www.notion.so](https://www.notion.so)\n\n---\n\n- **I rented my first apartment!**\n    \n    Did I rent an apartment? **[YES / NO]**, I did.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My roommate, Bill and I need household items.**\n    \n    Is my roommate named Bill? **[YES / NO]**, he is.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I need a bed.**\n    \n    *(Error en audio: dice “pillow” en lugar de “bed”)*\n    \n    Do I need a pillow? **[YES / NO]**, I don’t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I also need a table and chairs for the kitchen.**\n    \n    Do I need a coffee maker? **[YES / NO]**, I don\'t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Bill has a couch.**\n    \n    Does Bill have a couch? **[YES / NO]**, he does.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I think we need a chair for the living room.**\n    \n    Do I think we need a rug for the living room? **[YES / NO]**, I don’t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I need a large screen TV.**\n    \n    Do I need a large screen TV? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Bill disagrees.**\n    \n    Does Bill want a large screen TV too? **[YES / NO]**, he doesn’t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I need things to cook with too.**\n    \n    Do I need things to cook with? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **But Bill already has some.**\n    \n    Does Bill have some cooking items? **[YES / NO]**, he does.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **“Do you have pots and pans?” I ask.**\n    \n    Do I ask him if he has a coffee maker? **[YES / NO]**, I ask about pots and pans.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **“Yes. But I don\'t have any dishes.” Bill replies.**\n    \n    Does Bill have dishes? **[YES / NO]**, he doesn\'t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **At the home store, I buy dishes.**\n    \n    Do I buy the dishes? **[YES / NO]**, I do.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I ask Bill to buy forks and spoons.**\n    \n    Does Bill buy knives? **[YES / NO]**, he doesn\'t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I don\'t have bed sheets and towels.**\n    \n    Do I have bed sheets? **[YES / NO]**, I don\'t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Bill needs blankets.**\n    \n    Does Bill need towels? **[YES / NO]**, he doesn’t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Bill and I go to another store.**\n    \n    Does Bill go to another store with me? **[YES / NO]**, he does.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **There I buy bed sheets and three towels.**\n    \n    Do I buy six towels? **[YES / NO]**, I buy three.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I have very little money left.**\n    \n    Do I have a great amount of money? **[YES / NO]**, I don\'t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **And, I still don\'t have a bed!**\n    \n    Did I get a bed? **[YES / NO]**, I didn\'t.\n    \n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ IMPORTANTE\n\nSolo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder **todas las preguntas**:\n\n- En voz alta\n- A tiempo\n- Sin mirar el texto','[{\"label\":\"https:\\/\\/www.notion.so\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.notion.so\",\"description\":\"Enlace externo importado desde las notas.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+16+-+Household+Items+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/household-items\\/chapter1-story16-householditems-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+16+-+Household+Items+-+Normal+version (1).mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/household-items\\/chapter1-story16-householditems-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/household-items.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/household-items/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/household-items/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/household-items/subtitle-en.vtt',893,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:15','2026-05-08 08:04:15'),(132,2,'Time','time','Capítulo 1: Historias Interactivas [Yes/No]',2,20,'Tip: Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.','## ⏰ Time\n\n### Section 20 · Chapter 1\n\n**Tip:** Ve el video 2 veces para entender mejor la historia.\n\n---\n\n## 1️⃣ Escucha con traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha un par de veces hasta que entiendas bien la historia.\n\n🎧 **Audio 1 – Escucha con traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+17+-+Time+-+Normal+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/time/chapter1-story17-time-normalversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n- **I went to see a movie.**\n    \n    Fui a ver una película.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I arrived at the theater at 3:00 pm.**\n    \n    Llegué al cine a las tres de la tarde.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **But I was early.**\n    \n    Pero llegué pronto.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I asked the attendant, “What time does the movie start?”**\n    \n    Le pregunté al encargado: “¿A qué hora empieza la película?”.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **He told me, “The movie starts in thirty minutes.”**\n    \n    Me dijo: “La película empieza dentro de treinta minutos”.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I watched the movie.**\n    \n    Vi la película.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Later at home, I baked a chicken.**\n    \n    Más tarde, en casa, horneé un pollo.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I set the oven timer for one hour.**\n    \n    Programé el temporizador del horno para una hora.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My chicken finished cooking at 7:00 pm.**\n    \n    El pollo terminó de cocinarse a las siete de la tarde.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I fell asleep at 11:00 in the evening.**\n    \n    Me dormí a las once de la noche.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **But I woke up at midnight.**\n    \n    Pero me desperté a medianoche.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I was hungry.**\n    \n    Tenía hambre.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I knew I shouldn’t eat until morning.**\n    \n    Sabía que no debía comer hasta por la mañana.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I heard my alarm clock at 8:00 am.**\n    \n    Oí el despertador a las ocho de la mañana.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I hate mornings.**\n    \n    Odio las mañanas.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I drank a pot of coffee.**\n    \n    Me tomé un café.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I wanted to shop for clothes.**\n    \n    Quería comprar ropa.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I called the store and asked, “What time do you open?”**\n    \n    Llamé a la tienda y pregunté: “¿A qué hora abren?”.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **The clerk told me, “10 o’clock.”**\n    \n    El dependiente me dijo: “A las diez”.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I went to the store right away.**\n    \n    Fui a la tienda enseguida.\n    \n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Escucha sin traducción\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que entiendas la historia con los ojos cerrados.\n\n🎧 **Audio 2 – Escucha sin traducción**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+17+-+Time+-+Normal+version (1).mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/time/chapter1-story17-time-normalversion-1.mp3)\n\n---\n\nI went to see a movie.\n\nI arrived at the theater at 3:00 pm.\n\nBut I was early.\n\nI asked the attendant, “What time does the movie start?”\n\nHe told me, “The movie starts in thirty minutes.”\n\nI watched the movie.\n\nLater at home, I baked a chicken.\n\nI set the oven timer for one hour.\n\nMy chicken finished cooking at 7:00 pm.\n\nI fell asleep at 11:00 in the evening.\n\nBut I woke up at midnight.\n\nI was hungry.\n\nI knew I shouldn’t eat until morning.\n\nI heard my alarm clock at 8:00 am.\n\nI hate mornings.\n\nI drank a pot of coffee.\n\nI wanted to shop for clothes.\n\nI called the store and asked, “What time do you open?”\n\nThe clerk told me, “10 o\'clock.”\n\nI went to the store right away.\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Escucha y practica responder\n\n**Instrucciones:**\n\nEscucha varias veces hasta que puedas responder correctamente a todas las preguntas,\n\na tiempo, con los ojos cerrados y sin mirar el texto.\n\n🎧 **Audio 3 – Preguntas y respuestas**\n\n[Chapter+1+-+Story+17+-+Time+-+Interactive+version.mp3](/media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/time/chapter1-story17-time-interactiveversion.mp3)\n\n---\n\n- **I went to see a movie.**\n    \n    Did I go see my mother? **[YES / NO]**, I did not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I arrived at the theater at 3:00 pm.**\n    \n    Did I arrive at the theater at 3:00 am? **[YES / NO]**, I arrived at 3:00 pm.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **But I was early.**\n    \n    Was I early? **[YES / NO]**, I was.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I asked the attendant, “What time does the movie start?”**\n    \n    Did I ask what time the movie started? **[YES / NO]**, I did.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **He told me, “The movie starts in thirty minutes.”**\n    \n    Did the movie start in twenty minutes? **[YES / NO]**, it started in thirty minutes.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I watched the movie.**\n    \n    Did I watch the movie? **[YES / NO]**, I did.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **Later at home, I baked a chicken.**\n    \n    Later did I bake cookies? **[YES / NO]**, I baked a chicken.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I set the oven timer for one hour.**\n    \n    Did I set the timer for one hour? **[YES / NO]**, I did.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **My chicken finished cooking at 7:00 pm.**\n    \n    Was the chicken finished at 7:00 pm? **[YES / NO]**, it was.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I fell asleep at 11:00 in the evening.**\n    \n    Did I fall asleep at 10:00 in the morning? **[YES / NO]**, I didn\'t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **But I woke up at midnight.**\n    \n    Did I wake up at midnight? **[YES / NO]**, I did.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I was hungry.**\n    \n    Was I thirsty? **[YES / NO]**, I wasn\'t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I knew I shouldn\'t eat until morning.**\n    \n    Should I eat late at night? **[YES / NO]**, I should not.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I heard my alarm clock at 8:00 am.**\n    \n    Did I hear my alarm at 6:00 am? **[YES / NO]**, I didn’t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I hate mornings.**\n    \n    Do I like mornings? **[YES / NO]**, I don’t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I drank a pot of coffee.**\n    \n    Did I drink a cup of coffee? **[YES / NO]**, I didn\'t.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I wanted to shop for clothes.**\n    \n    Did I want to go shopping? **[YES / NO]**, I did.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I called the store and asked, “What time do you open?”**\n    \n    Did I ask what time the store opened? **[YES / NO]**, I did.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **The clerk told me, “10 o\'clock.”**\n    \n    Did the store open at 10:00 am? **[YES / NO]**, it did.\n    \n\n---\n\n- **I went to the store right away.**\n    \n    Did I wait to go to the store? **[YES / NO]**, I went right away.\n    \n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ IMPORTANTE\n\nSolo podrás continuar a la siguiente sección cuando logres responder **todas las preguntas**:\n\n- En voz alta\n- A tiempo\n- Sin mirar el texto','[{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+17+-+Time+-+Normal+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/time\\/chapter1-story17-time-normalversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+17+-+Time+-+Normal+version (1).mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/time\\/chapter1-story17-time-normalversion-1.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"},{\"label\":\"Chapter+1+-+Story+17+-+Time+-+Interactive+version.mp3\",\"url\":\"\\/media\\/imported\\/curso-de-ingles-raio\\/time\\/chapter1-story17-time-interactiveversion.mp3\",\"description\":\"Archivo adjunto de la lecci\\u00f3n.\"}]','/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/htdocs/CURSO_RAIO/storage/app/course-media/curso-de-ingles-raio/time.mp4','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/time/poster.jpg','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/time/subtitle-es.vtt','media/imported/curso-de-ingles-raio/time/subtitle-en.vtt',812,1,'2026-05-08 08:04:15','2026-05-08 08:04:15');
